1
00:00:30,167 --> 00:00:35,560
** [ Fanfare ]

2
00:00:35,647 --> 00:00:37,478
[ Narrator ]
Young people from all over the globe...

3
00:00:37,567 --> 00:00:39,364
are joining up
to fight for the future.

4
00:00:39,447 --> 00:00:42,120
- I'm doing my part.
- I'm doing my part.

5
00:00:42,207 --> 00:00:43,925
I'm doing my part.

6
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:45,719
I'm doing my part too!

7
00:00:45,767 --> 00:00:47,644
[ Laughter ]

8
00:00:47,687 --> 00:00:49,564
They're doing their part. Are you?

9
00:00:49,647 --> 00:00:53,925
Join the Mobile Infantry and save the
world. Service guarantees citizenship.

10
00:00:58,367 --> 00:01:01,200
The Bugs send another meteor our way.

11
00:01:01,247 --> 00:01:05,399
But this time, we're ready.
Planetary defences are better than ever.

12
00:01:10,727 --> 00:01:13,161
Klendathu, source of the Bug
meteor attacks...

13
00:01:13,247 --> 00:01:16,557
orbits a twin star system
whose brutal gravitational forces...

14
00:01:16,607 --> 00:01:21,806
produce an unlimited supply
of Bug meteorites in the form
of this asteroid belt.

15
00:01:21,887 --> 00:01:24,879
To ensure the safety
of our solar system...

16
00:01:24,927 --> 00:01:26,804
Klendathu must be eliminated.

17
00:01:28,287 --> 00:01:31,120
We break net now and take you live
to Klendathu...

18
00:01:31,167 --> 00:01:33,681
where the invasion has begun!

19
00:01:33,727 --> 00:01:36,924
[ Man ] D XQ uplink on.
Two, one... you're on!

20
00:01:36,967 --> 00:01:41,563
We've just landed here on what
cap troopers are calling Big "K"...

21
00:01:41,647 --> 00:01:44,207
with the Sixth Mobile
Infantry Division.

22
00:01:44,287 --> 00:01:47,404
- It's an ugly planet, a Bug planet...
- [ Roaring ]

23
00:01:47,487 --> 00:01:50,638
a planet hostile to life
as we know it--

24
00:01:50,687 --> 00:01:53,360
Aaaah!

25
00:01:53,407 --> 00:01:55,762
Help me!
Aaaah!

26
00:01:55,807 --> 00:01:58,241
- Go!
- We've got to keep moving!

27
00:01:58,327 --> 00:02:01,399
[ Screaming Continues ]

28
00:02:01,447 --> 00:02:04,007
- [ Gunfire ]
- [ Roaring ]

29
00:02:04,087 --> 00:02:07,318
- Die! Die!
- Come on!
- Go! Go! Go!

30
00:02:07,407 --> 00:02:09,523
- Keep moving!
- Get out of here now!

31
00:02:09,567 --> 00:02:12,604
- [ Troopers Yelling, Indistinct ]
- [ Roaring Continues ]

32
00:02:12,647 --> 00:02:16,117
Run! Run!
Run! Run!

33
00:02:16,167 --> 00:02:18,635
[ Screaming ]

34
00:02:18,687 --> 00:02:20,678
Kitten! No!

35
00:02:20,767 --> 00:02:22,962
[ Screaming ]

36
00:02:25,207 --> 00:02:28,597
Aaah--

37
00:02:30,247 --> 00:02:32,363
[ Gasping, Groaning ]

38
00:02:32,447 --> 00:02:34,836
[ Screaming ]

39
00:02:48,127 --> 00:02:50,197
[ Man ]
Rico.

40
00:02:50,287 --> 00:02:52,323
Rico.

41
00:02:52,407 --> 00:02:54,762
Rico!

42
00:02:56,047 --> 00:02:58,003
Pay attention.

43
00:02:58,047 --> 00:03:00,607
Sorry, Mr Rasczak.

44
00:03:00,687 --> 00:03:05,203
Let's sum up. This year,
we explored the failure of democracy...

45
00:03:05,247 --> 00:03:08,796
how the social scientists brought
our world to the brink of chaos.

46
00:03:08,887 --> 00:03:11,845
We talked about the veterans,
how they took control...

47
00:03:11,927 --> 00:03:14,760
and imposed the stability
that has lasted for generations since.

48
00:03:14,847 --> 00:03:17,805
You know these facts.

49
00:03:17,887 --> 00:03:21,721
But have I taught you anything
of value this year? Hmm?

50
00:03:21,807 --> 00:03:24,321
You. Why are only citizens
allowed to vote?

51
00:03:24,407 --> 00:03:27,797
It's a reward-- what the Federation
gives you for doing Federal Service.

52
00:03:27,847 --> 00:03:29,963
No. No.

53
00:03:30,047 --> 00:03:33,084
Something given has no value.

54
00:03:33,127 --> 00:03:36,756
When you vote, you are
exercising political authority.

55
00:03:36,847 --> 00:03:38,678
You're using force.

56
00:03:38,767 --> 00:03:40,598
Force, my friends, is violence...

57
00:03:40,687 --> 00:03:44,396
the supreme authority from which
all other authority is derived.

58
00:03:44,447 --> 00:03:47,439
Uh, my mother always said
violence never solves anything.

59
00:03:47,527 --> 00:03:48,926
Really?

60
00:03:49,007 --> 00:03:52,363
I wonder what the city fathers
of Hiroshima would say about that.

61
00:03:52,447 --> 00:03:54,244
You.

62
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:58,280
They probably wouldn't say anything.
Hiroshima was destroyed.

63
00:03:58,367 --> 00:04:01,518
Correct. Naked force
has resolved more issues...

64
00:04:01,607 --> 00:04:03,438
throughout history
than any other factor.

65
00:04:03,487 --> 00:04:06,877
The contrary opinion,
that violence never solves anything...

66
00:04:06,967 --> 00:04:09,322
is wishful thinking
at its worst.

67
00:04:09,367 --> 00:04:12,040
People who forget that
always pay.

68
00:04:12,087 --> 00:04:15,636
Rico, what's the moral difference,
if any...

69
00:04:15,727 --> 00:04:18,366
between a civilian
and a citizen?

70
00:04:18,447 --> 00:04:22,326
A citizen accepts personal
responsibility for the safety
of the body politic...

71
00:04:22,407 --> 00:04:24,477
defending it with his life.

72
00:04:24,567 --> 00:04:28,606
- A civilian does not.
- Exact words of the text.

73
00:04:28,687 --> 00:04:31,440
But do you understand it?
Do you believe it?

74
00:04:32,607 --> 00:04:35,326
- I don't know.
- Of course you don't.

75
00:04:35,407 --> 00:04:37,523
I doubt anyone here
would recognize civic virtue...

76
00:04:37,607 --> 00:04:41,361
if it reached up
and bit you in the ass.

77
00:04:41,447 --> 00:04:43,438
[ Bell Rings ]

78
00:04:43,527 --> 00:04:46,280
- [ Students Chattering ]
- [ Chuckles ]

79
00:04:56,367 --> 00:04:58,358
Not here.

80
00:04:58,447 --> 00:05:00,438
Come on. Let's see
if they posted the math final.

81
00:05:00,527 --> 00:05:03,724
- Rico. We gonna take Tesla?
- We're gonna kill 'em.

82
00:05:06,127 --> 00:05:08,880
[ Woman On P.A. ] Remember,
all graduating seniors must go--

83
00:05:08,967 --> 00:05:11,561
First thing Fleet Academy looks at
is your math scores.

84
00:05:11,607 --> 00:05:13,484
Wish me luck.

85
00:05:17,927 --> 00:05:21,203
- [ Beep ]
- [ Student ] Way to go.

86
00:05:21,287 --> 00:05:24,518
- Good job.
- [ Chuckles ] Your turn.

87
00:05:24,567 --> 00:05:26,444
Hold on.
I want to talk to Marco.

88
00:05:26,487 --> 00:05:28,796
- His sister's at Fleet. Marco!
- Hi, Carmen.

89
00:05:28,847 --> 00:05:32,522
- [ Carmen ]
What'd you hear about Roxie?
- [ Marco ] She made pilot.

90
00:05:32,607 --> 00:05:34,882
[ Beep ]

91
00:05:34,927 --> 00:05:36,804
Thirty-five percent!

92
00:05:36,847 --> 00:05:38,405
Very nice.

93
00:05:38,447 --> 00:05:41,166
- Look at that!
- [ Students Laughing, Applauding ]

94
00:05:41,207 --> 00:05:43,562
Thirty-five percent,
ladies and gentlemen.

95
00:05:43,607 --> 00:05:46,121
- Big numbers.
- Carl!

96
00:05:46,167 --> 00:05:48,044
Sorry.

97
00:05:48,087 --> 00:05:49,964
[ Students Continue Chattering ]

98
00:05:53,327 --> 00:05:55,887
So, you haven't done it yet,
have you? Don't lie!

99
00:05:55,967 --> 00:05:58,720
I'm not in any hurry.

100
00:05:58,767 --> 00:06:00,962
Others are waiting.

101
00:06:01,007 --> 00:06:02,759
- [ Giggling ]
- Did you read her mind?

102
00:06:02,847 --> 00:06:06,556
Don't have to.
It's pretty clear what she wants.

103
00:06:06,607 --> 00:06:08,484
Yeah, but I want Carmen.

104
00:06:08,527 --> 00:06:11,963
Aw, you got it bad.
Hey, don't forget about this afternoon.

105
00:06:12,047 --> 00:06:14,277
He's always late when he
walks you home to fish for a kiss.

106
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:16,676
[ Laughs ]
Get out of here.

107
00:06:16,727 --> 00:06:19,878
- Marco's sister made pilot!
- So will you.

108
00:06:19,927 --> 00:06:23,715
I mean, imagine flying
a half a million tons of starship.

109
00:06:23,807 --> 00:06:25,684
You gotta have nerves of steel.

110
00:06:25,767 --> 00:06:28,235
Yeah, you do.
Let's see how yours hold up.

111
00:06:28,327 --> 00:06:30,238
[ Woman ]
You may begin!

112
00:06:35,167 --> 00:06:36,998
[ Grunts ]

113
00:06:37,087 --> 00:06:38,486
[ Groans ]

114
00:06:38,567 --> 00:06:41,320
- Ohh.
- Oh, come on. It's just a bug.

115
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:44,200
- Better put your goggles on.
-Just a bug. Ha!

116
00:06:44,287 --> 00:06:47,916
We humans like to think we are
nature's finest achievement.

117
00:06:48,007 --> 00:06:50,396
I'm afraid it just isn't true.

118
00:06:50,447 --> 00:06:54,759
This Arkellian Sand Beetle
is superior in many ways.

119
00:06:54,847 --> 00:06:58,237
It reproduces in vast numbers...

120
00:06:58,287 --> 00:07:01,324
has no ego, has no fear...

121
00:07:01,407 --> 00:07:03,398
doesn't know about death...

122
00:07:03,447 --> 00:07:06,803
and, so, is the perfect,
selfless member of society.

123
00:07:06,887 --> 00:07:11,085
But humans have created art,
mathematics and interstellar travel.

124
00:07:11,167 --> 00:07:13,044
[ Gulps ]

125
00:07:13,127 --> 00:07:16,961
True, but before you
let that go to your head,
take the example of the Arachnids...

126
00:07:17,007 --> 00:07:20,682
a highly evolved
insect society.

127
00:07:20,767 --> 00:07:23,645
By human standards
they are relatively stupid...

128
00:07:23,727 --> 00:07:27,720
but their evolution
stretches over millions of years.

129
00:07:27,767 --> 00:07:32,477
-And now they can colonize planets...
- Here. Take this.

130
00:07:32,527 --> 00:07:35,087
by hurling their spore
into space.

131
00:07:35,167 --> 00:07:36,998
[ Rico ]
Yeah, I think we got it.

132
00:07:37,087 --> 00:07:40,523
- There's the heart...
- [ Gulping ]

133
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:43,081
and here's the stomach.

134
00:07:43,127 --> 00:07:45,083
[ Laughing ]

135
00:07:45,167 --> 00:07:47,442
[ Coughing ]

136
00:07:47,527 --> 00:07:50,599
[ Dizzy ]
Nerves of steel, huh? [ Laughs ]

137
00:07:50,647 --> 00:07:53,207
[ Computer Beeps ]

138
00:07:53,287 --> 00:07:56,484
[ Sighs ] Don't think about it.
Just go on instinct.

139
00:07:56,527 --> 00:07:58,404
Try to visualize it.

140
00:08:12,127 --> 00:08:14,561
I see the ace of spades.

141
00:08:14,607 --> 00:08:16,996
[ Computer Beeps ]

142
00:08:17,087 --> 00:08:18,918
Uhh.

143
00:08:18,967 --> 00:08:22,118
Statistically speaking, you should have
accidentally guessed right by now.

144
00:08:22,207 --> 00:08:24,198
[ Yawns ]
Try another.

145
00:08:24,247 --> 00:08:26,203
So, my psychic abilities
are zero and I'm unlucky.

146
00:08:26,287 --> 00:08:29,324
- [ Computer Beeps ]
- No, luck's not a factor.

147
00:08:29,367 --> 00:08:32,598
No one really knows why some people
are sensitive and some aren't.

148
00:08:32,687 --> 00:08:35,247
Who knows? Maybe it's
a new stage of human evolution.

149
00:08:35,287 --> 00:08:38,245
That's why they do
these kind of Federal studies.

150
00:08:38,287 --> 00:08:41,165
Cyrano!
Ah, shit. Time out.

151
00:08:41,207 --> 00:08:44,199
Aw, he just wants some attention.
You don't play with him any more.

152
00:08:44,247 --> 00:08:46,681
Cyrano!

153
00:08:47,727 --> 00:08:50,525
- Go bug Mom, Cyrano.
- [ Chitters ]

154
00:08:58,687 --> 00:09:00,996
How do you make him do that?

155
00:09:01,087 --> 00:09:04,875
Oh, I gave him the impression
there's a grub crawling up my mom's leg.

156
00:09:04,967 --> 00:09:06,798
He's on a mission
to go eat it.

157
00:09:06,887 --> 00:09:09,003
- [ Mom ] Oh! Get off my leg.
- [ Chittering, Metal Clanging ]

158
00:09:09,047 --> 00:09:12,278
[ Mom ]
Oh! Carl!

159
00:09:13,487 --> 00:09:16,206
I sure hope you don't do
anything like that to me.

160
00:09:16,287 --> 00:09:21,077
Don't be afraid.
Can't do human. Yet.

161
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:23,158
[ Crowd Screaming, Cheering ]

162
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:30,198
All right!

163
00:09:36,287 --> 00:09:38,403
Yeah! Yeah!

164
00:09:38,447 --> 00:09:41,883
[ Announcer ]
The score is now 41 to 38.

165
00:09:41,967 --> 00:09:45,846
Tigers lead with 2.:46 remaining
here at the Buenos Aires Sports Arena.

166
00:09:45,927 --> 00:09:49,283
- Time out.: Giants.
- Are you all right?

167
00:09:49,327 --> 00:09:52,637
- Much better now.
- Good.

168
00:09:52,687 --> 00:09:55,155
[ Crowd, Team Cheering ]

169
00:09:55,247 --> 00:09:58,398
Hey! Your helmet!

170
00:09:58,447 --> 00:10:00,517
So, what are you doing
after the game?

171
00:10:00,567 --> 00:10:05,004
[ Laughs ] Well, everyone's
going to the dance. Aren't you?

172
00:10:05,087 --> 00:10:08,204
- I don't know.
It's my last night as a civilian.
- Number 12, let's go!

173
00:10:08,287 --> 00:10:10,118
Ship off to Tereshkova tomorrow.

174
00:10:10,207 --> 00:10:13,802
- You're going to the Fleet Academy?
- Uh-huh.

175
00:10:13,847 --> 00:10:18,079
- That's where I want to go!
- [ Man ] Come on, number 12!
Let's play ball.

176
00:10:18,127 --> 00:10:20,595
Don't get any ideas
about my girlfriend!

177
00:10:23,207 --> 00:10:25,323
All is fair in love and war.

178
00:10:26,567 --> 00:10:29,639
- Giants! Giants!
-Johnny! Yeah!

179
00:10:29,687 --> 00:10:31,723
Hut! Hut!

180
00:10:36,087 --> 00:10:38,555
[ Cheerleaders Cheering ]

181
00:10:41,607 --> 00:10:43,882
- Woo!
- Take that!

182
00:10:43,927 --> 00:10:48,125
[ Announcer ]
Just under 22 seconds remaining.

183
00:10:49,807 --> 00:10:51,877
- [ Crowd Cheering ]
- Yeah!

184
00:10:51,967 --> 00:10:54,356
[ Dizzy ] All right, let's go.
Irving, Latham, cover the rook.

185
00:10:54,447 --> 00:10:58,122
Perry, fake left.
Ricoli, you go long.

186
00:10:58,167 --> 00:11:00,522
Rico, flip six, three hole.
Got it?

187
00:11:00,567 --> 00:11:02,444
Hey! Rico!

188
00:11:02,527 --> 00:11:04,006
- Hey!
- What?

189
00:11:04,047 --> 00:11:07,483
You're drifting!
Flip six, three hole on one. Got it?

190
00:11:07,567 --> 00:11:09,319
Just throw me the ball, Diz.

191
00:11:09,407 --> 00:11:11,716
- Ready? Break!
- [ Team Grunts ]

192
00:11:13,247 --> 00:11:15,363
[ Diz Shouting ]
Two! Six!

193
00:11:15,407 --> 00:11:17,284
- Climb left!
- Screen!

194
00:11:17,327 --> 00:11:19,204
Hut!

195
00:11:29,087 --> 00:11:32,159
- [ Crowd Cheering ]
- Yeah! Go! Go! Go!

196
00:11:34,967 --> 00:11:36,958
All right!

197
00:11:38,287 --> 00:11:40,642
- [ Buzzer Sounds ]
- [ Cheering Continues ]
- Yeah!

198
00:11:40,687 --> 00:11:44,566
[ Blows Whistle ]
He's in there! It's over!

199
00:11:45,967 --> 00:11:48,686
** [ Marching Band ]

200
00:11:51,167 --> 00:11:54,557
[ Shouting ]

201
00:11:59,887 --> 00:12:02,242
Who said you could
grow up so fast?

202
00:12:02,287 --> 00:12:04,357
Mom, don't get mushy.

203
00:12:05,927 --> 00:12:10,125
This came for you today.
I presume, at your request.

204
00:12:13,287 --> 00:12:15,562
A lot of my friends
are doing Federal Service.

205
00:12:15,647 --> 00:12:17,877
Well, you're not
thinking of applying?

206
00:12:17,967 --> 00:12:20,037
Have you lost your mind?

207
00:12:20,087 --> 00:12:23,204
I'd rather take ten lashes in Public
Square than see you ruin your life.

208
00:12:23,247 --> 00:12:27,399
It's a term of service.
It's not a career.

209
00:12:27,487 --> 00:12:30,763
I just want
to get out on my own...

210
00:12:30,807 --> 00:12:33,241
see the galaxy
for a couple of years.

211
00:12:33,327 --> 00:12:35,716
Johnny, people get killed
in the Federal Service.

212
00:12:35,807 --> 00:12:39,038
Who gave you this idea?
It's that teacher, isn't it?

213
00:12:39,087 --> 00:12:43,080
What's his name?
You know the one I'm talking about.

214
00:12:43,127 --> 00:12:45,482
Mr Rasczak.

215
00:12:45,567 --> 00:12:47,398
Rasczak?

216
00:12:47,487 --> 00:12:49,796
[ Chuckles ]
Silly name.

217
00:12:49,847 --> 00:12:52,520
There should be a law against using
a school as a recruiting station.

218
00:12:52,607 --> 00:12:56,600
No. Rasczak doesn't
do that at all.

219
00:12:56,687 --> 00:12:58,917
He sort of discourages you.

220
00:12:58,967 --> 00:13:03,245
Well, that's good, 'cause you're going
to Harvard and that's the end of it.

221
00:13:03,327 --> 00:13:06,160
It's my decision not yours.

222
00:13:06,247 --> 00:13:09,000
- Oh, is that how it is?
- Wait, you two.

223
00:13:09,047 --> 00:13:12,198
Dad and I have a surprise for you
that will settle this.

224
00:13:12,287 --> 00:13:15,324
- Can you guess what it is?
- No.

225
00:13:16,967 --> 00:13:19,720
You wanted to see the galaxy?

226
00:13:19,807 --> 00:13:22,844
How about a trip
to the Outer Rings?

227
00:13:22,927 --> 00:13:25,805
Zegema Beach. Huh?

228
00:13:28,047 --> 00:13:31,084
- I've always wanted to go there.
- Good. Then it's all settled.

229
00:13:34,607 --> 00:13:40,637
[ Rock ]
* Into it, into your head *

230
00:13:40,687 --> 00:13:43,247
* Save it
Sell one *

231
00:13:43,327 --> 00:13:45,966
* Mix it
Hang these *

232
00:13:46,047 --> 00:13:48,322
* Leftover waste--**

233
00:13:48,367 --> 00:13:51,006
Sure. Don't go away.

234
00:13:51,087 --> 00:13:53,123
[ Rico ]
I'm just gonna go see Mr Rasczak.

235
00:13:54,447 --> 00:13:56,324
Hey, Rico.
You wanna dance?

236
00:13:56,367 --> 00:13:58,244
Actually, Diz,
I promised Carmen--

237
00:13:58,287 --> 00:14:00,517
Aw, come on. Too bad for her.
She's not around.

238
00:14:03,647 --> 00:14:08,482
It's sad-- after tonight, most of us
probably won't see each other again.

239
00:14:11,727 --> 00:14:13,797
So, you still gonna play for Rio?

240
00:14:15,567 --> 00:14:18,081
Yeah, looks like.
Unless Tokyo lets me start.

241
00:14:18,127 --> 00:14:21,517
Well, anyone who gets you is lucky.

242
00:14:21,607 --> 00:14:24,280
Johnny, how come
we never got together?

243
00:14:28,087 --> 00:14:29,964
Can't we just be friends, Diz?

244
00:14:32,047 --> 00:14:33,924
Sure.

245
00:14:35,887 --> 00:14:39,243
- Okeydokey.
- Nice seeing you.

246
00:14:39,287 --> 00:14:42,916
Look, Diz,
I want to talk to Mr Rasczak.

247
00:14:45,167 --> 00:14:47,476
Well, you'd better hurry up
if you want to catch him.

248
00:14:47,567 --> 00:14:49,398
You're the best.

249
00:14:53,127 --> 00:14:55,004
Hey.

250
00:14:55,087 --> 00:14:56,918
[ Chuckles ]

251
00:15:01,487 --> 00:15:04,638
- Mr Rasczak!
- What is it, Rico?

252
00:15:04,687 --> 00:15:08,282
I want to thank you. Your class
was the best one I had this year.

253
00:15:08,367 --> 00:15:11,165
Well, it's really not my job to please.
I just hope you learned something.

254
00:15:11,247 --> 00:15:14,683
I want to join up. I think
I got what it takes to be a citizen.

255
00:15:14,767 --> 00:15:16,997
Good for you.
Go find out.

256
00:15:17,087 --> 00:15:20,557
Well, my parents are against it.
I know it's my choice.

257
00:15:20,647 --> 00:15:24,799
I was wondering.
What would you do if you were me?

258
00:15:24,847 --> 00:15:28,362
Figuring things out for yourself
is the only freedom anyone really has.

259
00:15:28,407 --> 00:15:32,036
Use that freedom.
Make up your own mind, Rico.

260
00:15:32,087 --> 00:15:36,160
* [ Light Salsa ]

261
00:15:36,207 --> 00:15:38,596
* Ah-oh *

262
00:15:38,647 --> 00:15:41,115
* But I have not been
to paradise *

263
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:43,044
* Ah-lay-oh *

264
00:15:43,087 --> 00:15:48,036
* No, I have not been
to paradise *

265
00:15:48,087 --> 00:15:50,840
* Watch the days go by *

266
00:15:50,927 --> 00:15:52,758
* All is well *

267
00:15:52,847 --> 00:15:55,281
[ Carmen Laughing ]
Don't exaggerate.

268
00:15:55,367 --> 00:15:57,323
You have really
beautiful eyes.

269
00:15:57,367 --> 00:15:59,244
Johnny!

270
00:16:01,647 --> 00:16:05,481
- This is Zander.
- Yeah, we know
each other from the game.

271
00:16:06,807 --> 00:16:10,356
- No hard feelings?
- Oh, none at all. We won.

272
00:16:10,447 --> 00:16:12,802
Come on, Carmen.

273
00:16:12,847 --> 00:16:14,917
It's the last dance.

274
00:16:14,967 --> 00:16:17,322
Well, maybe I'll see you
at the Academy.

275
00:16:17,407 --> 00:16:19,716
Yeah. Who knows?

276
00:16:19,767 --> 00:16:21,405
Good luck.

277
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:26,077
- [ Sighs ]
- Zander's going for pilot too.

278
00:16:26,127 --> 00:16:28,641
You two have so much in common.

279
00:16:28,687 --> 00:16:31,679
Johnny Rico.
Are you jealous?

280
00:16:31,727 --> 00:16:34,287
Well, maybe.

281
00:16:34,367 --> 00:16:36,358
You don't have to be jealous.

282
00:16:36,447 --> 00:16:39,325
* No, I have not been
to paradise *

283
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:42,444
Hey, hey!
Break it up, you two!

284
00:16:42,487 --> 00:16:44,557
There's a place
for that sort of thing.

285
00:16:44,647 --> 00:16:47,400
[ Sighs ]

286
00:16:47,447 --> 00:16:50,678
I've been thinking,
and I'm gonna do it, Carmen.

287
00:16:50,767 --> 00:16:52,997
I'm gonna go for Federal Service.

288
00:16:53,047 --> 00:16:58,121
That's great! Carl and I
are signing up tomorrow. Come with us.

289
00:16:58,207 --> 00:17:00,038
I will.

290
00:17:00,127 --> 00:17:05,076
* Walk about
Watch the days go by *

291
00:17:05,167 --> 00:17:08,204
My father's not home tonight.

292
00:17:09,247 --> 00:17:11,283
* All is well *

293
00:17:13,687 --> 00:17:18,363
* All is well *

294
00:17:18,447 --> 00:17:23,123
* Talk about
Watch the days go by *

295
00:17:23,207 --> 00:17:25,482
* All is well *

296
00:17:25,567 --> 00:17:27,956
* Twenty-third century guys *

297
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:29,878
* All is well **

298
00:17:29,967 --> 00:17:31,798
[ Recruits ]
...of my own free will...

299
00:17:31,887 --> 00:17:34,640
after having been duly advised
and warned...

300
00:17:34,727 --> 00:17:37,924
of the meaning and consequences
of this oath...

301
00:17:37,967 --> 00:17:42,358
enrol in the Federal Service
for not less than two years...

302
00:17:42,447 --> 00:17:47,521
and as much longer as may be required
by the needs of the Federation.

303
00:17:49,727 --> 00:17:51,558
Thank you.

304
00:17:54,487 --> 00:17:58,446
Fresh meat for the grinder, eh?

305
00:17:58,527 --> 00:18:02,202
- So, how'd you kids do?
- I'm gonna be a pilot.

306
00:18:02,287 --> 00:18:06,121
Well, good for you.
We need all the pilots we can get.

307
00:18:07,687 --> 00:18:10,520
- Hey, did you get Starside R&D?
- No.

308
00:18:10,607 --> 00:18:13,917
- I don't believe it.
- I got Games and Theory.

309
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:17,721
Games and Theory?
That's Military Intelligence.

310
00:18:17,807 --> 00:18:20,844
Way to go, Carl.

311
00:18:20,887 --> 00:18:23,526
Next time we meet,
I'll probably have to salute you.

312
00:18:23,567 --> 00:18:25,080
Hmm.

313
00:18:26,167 --> 00:18:28,158
What about you, son?

314
00:18:28,207 --> 00:18:31,005
- Infantry, sir.
- Good for you.

315
00:18:31,087 --> 00:18:33,965
Mobile Infantry
made me the man I am today.

316
00:18:36,407 --> 00:18:40,764
[ P.A. ] All recruits report
to the Federal Transportation
Hub within 2 4 hours.

317
00:18:40,847 --> 00:18:42,917
- Welcome to the adventure
of Federal Service.
- [ Laughing ]

318
00:18:43,007 --> 00:18:45,237
Let's make a vow.

319
00:18:45,327 --> 00:18:49,002
No matter what,
we'll always be friends.

320
00:18:50,287 --> 00:18:52,926
I'll go for that.

321
00:18:53,007 --> 00:18:55,362
Well, chances are
we'll never see each other again.

322
00:18:57,207 --> 00:18:59,846
We'll be millions of light-years
away from each other.

323
00:18:59,887 --> 00:19:02,447
But, uh, yeah, sure.
Why not?

324
00:19:04,527 --> 00:19:06,677
You'll resign.
That's all there is to it!

325
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:09,486
It may look bad, but if that's
the worst you suffer, then that's fine.

326
00:19:09,567 --> 00:19:12,400
- I won't quit.
- I'm telling you, you will.

327
00:19:12,487 --> 00:19:14,443
You're not going back.
You're going on vacation!

328
00:19:14,527 --> 00:19:17,803
I am not going on vacation!
I want to be a citizen.

329
00:19:17,847 --> 00:19:19,724
My decision.
I made it.

330
00:19:19,767 --> 00:19:23,396
You walk out that door, you are cut off,
young man. You understand me?

331
00:19:23,487 --> 00:19:25,398
All right! That's it!
You are cut off!

332
00:19:25,487 --> 00:19:27,318
Johnny, why won't you
change your mind?

333
00:19:27,407 --> 00:19:30,444
Does citizenship
mean that much to you?

334
00:19:30,487 --> 00:19:32,523
Well, yeah. Sure.

335
00:19:32,567 --> 00:19:34,444
I hope so.

336
00:19:34,487 --> 00:19:36,842
I hope you don't ruin your life
over some silly little girl...

337
00:19:36,927 --> 00:19:38,963
who wants to look handsome
in a uniform.

338
00:19:39,047 --> 00:19:41,959
- Don't talk about Carmen that way!
-Johnny!

339
00:19:42,047 --> 00:19:44,925
[ Woman On P.A. ] Your attention,
please. Outbound troops 13-A--

340
00:19:45,007 --> 00:19:47,362
[ P.A. Continues, Indistinct ]

341
00:19:47,407 --> 00:19:50,444
[ Man ]
Do you have everything? Great.

342
00:19:56,127 --> 00:19:57,958
[ Carmen ]
Johnny.

343
00:19:59,567 --> 00:20:02,127
- You're late.
- My dad had to help me pack.

344
00:20:02,207 --> 00:20:05,165
Suddenly, he's afraid he's never
gonna see me again or something.

345
00:20:05,247 --> 00:20:09,001
It was sweet,
but it took forever. Ohh.

346
00:20:09,087 --> 00:20:11,885
Anyway, I guess
I'm ready to go.

347
00:20:11,927 --> 00:20:14,760
Yeah, me, too.
I'm wearing everything I own.

348
00:20:17,647 --> 00:20:19,524
I'm sorry your parents were mad.

349
00:20:19,567 --> 00:20:21,444
Who cares?

350
00:20:21,487 --> 00:20:24,365
The Federation'll give me everything
I need for the next two years, right?

351
00:20:25,327 --> 00:20:27,158
You talk to Carl?

352
00:20:27,247 --> 00:20:31,206
Yeah, he left this morning.
Couldn't say where.

353
00:20:31,247 --> 00:20:33,124
Oh, it's exciting going away.

354
00:20:33,167 --> 00:20:35,840
But I'm scared.
Aren't you?

355
00:20:35,887 --> 00:20:37,957
[ Sighs ]

356
00:20:39,727 --> 00:20:42,446
I'm gonna miss you.

357
00:20:43,687 --> 00:20:45,962
I'm gonna miss you too.

358
00:20:46,047 --> 00:20:48,038
I love you.

359
00:20:48,087 --> 00:20:51,841
[ Woman On P.A. ] Outbound group 94-A,
Tereshkova, all sections--

360
00:20:51,887 --> 00:20:53,764
That's me.

361
00:20:55,767 --> 00:20:59,680
Just say it once.
Try it on for size.

362
00:21:03,087 --> 00:21:04,964
I love you.

363
00:21:12,607 --> 00:21:15,917
- Don't forget to write.
- I won't.

364
00:21:26,007 --> 00:21:29,158
** [ Fanfare ]

365
00:21:30,407 --> 00:21:33,240
Fully automatic Morita.
Who wants to hold it?

366
00:21:33,327 --> 00:21:35,636
- Me! Me!
- [ Narrator ] Citizen rule.

367
00:21:35,727 --> 00:21:38,844
People making a better tomorrow.

368
00:21:38,927 --> 00:21:40,758
- Pow!
- Mine!
- Gimme!

369
00:21:40,847 --> 00:21:42,599
[ Laughing ]

370
00:21:46,447 --> 00:21:49,723
A murderer was captured
this morning and tried today.

371
00:21:49,807 --> 00:21:53,083
Guilty.

372
00:21:53,167 --> 00:21:56,204
Sentence.: death.
Execution.: tonight at 6.:00.

373
00:22:05,407 --> 00:22:08,365
If you think you're psychic...

374
00:22:08,407 --> 00:22:10,284
maybe you are.

375
00:22:11,727 --> 00:22:14,764
Federal studies are being
conducted in your community.

376
00:22:17,767 --> 00:22:21,157
Every school kid knows
that Arachnids are dangerous.

377
00:22:21,247 --> 00:22:23,078
[ Screeching ]

378
00:22:27,087 --> 00:22:29,965
However, Mormon extremists
disregarded Federal warnings...

379
00:22:30,007 --> 00:22:34,125
and established Port Joe Smith deep
inside the Arachnid Quarantine Zone.

380
00:22:34,167 --> 00:22:38,240
Too late, they realized that
Dantana had already been chosen
by other colonists--

381
00:22:38,287 --> 00:22:40,164
Arachnids.

382
00:22:44,607 --> 00:22:47,565
[ Cadets ]
One, two, three, four!

383
00:22:47,647 --> 00:22:49,478
One, two, three, four!

384
00:22:49,567 --> 00:22:53,480
[ Man ] Most of you will not live
to be in the Mobile Infantry.

385
00:22:53,527 --> 00:22:56,280
The trouble is, you are not
good enough the way you are.

386
00:22:56,367 --> 00:22:58,198
Hands at your side!

387
00:22:58,287 --> 00:23:02,519
Chin up! I am your senior
drill instructor, Career Sergeant Zim.

388
00:23:02,607 --> 00:23:04,802
Suck in that gut!

389
00:23:04,847 --> 00:23:06,519
Feet together!

390
00:23:07,887 --> 00:23:11,562
To think this had to happen to me.
What a bunch of apes.

391
00:23:11,647 --> 00:23:14,445
No, strike that!
You don't rate that good!

392
00:23:14,487 --> 00:23:16,000
Never in my life have I seen--

393
00:23:17,087 --> 00:23:20,079
- [ Chuckling ]
- Do you think I'm funny?

394
00:23:20,167 --> 00:23:23,318
- Do I make you laugh?
Do you think I'm a comedian, son?
- I'm sorry.

395
00:23:23,407 --> 00:23:27,366
The first words and the last words out
of your stinking holes will be "sir"!

396
00:23:27,407 --> 00:23:29,477
- Do you get me?
- Sir, yes, sir!

397
00:23:29,567 --> 00:23:31,523
See that armoury?
Run around it!

398
00:23:31,567 --> 00:23:34,320
- [ Groans ]
- Run, I said! Run! Run! Run!

399
00:23:34,407 --> 00:23:36,557
- Bronski, keep pace!
- Move!

400
00:23:36,647 --> 00:23:38,763
[ Zim ] Now, any time
you think I'm being too tough...

401
00:23:38,807 --> 00:23:41,162
any time you think
I'm being unfair...

402
00:23:41,207 --> 00:23:44,040
any time you miss your mommy, quit!

403
00:23:44,087 --> 00:23:49,002
You sign form 1240-A,
you grab your gear, you take
a stroll down Washout Lane.

404
00:23:49,047 --> 00:23:51,959
- Do you get me?
- Sir, yes, sir!

405
00:23:52,047 --> 00:23:56,643
Pathetic! I wonder if there's a handful
of guts in the whole bunch of you.

406
00:23:56,687 --> 00:23:58,564
Now...

407
00:23:58,607 --> 00:24:01,405
who here thinks they got
what it takes to knock me down?

408
00:24:01,487 --> 00:24:04,843
Sir, I guess maybe I do, sir!

409
00:24:10,527 --> 00:24:12,358
[ Growls ]

410
00:24:12,447 --> 00:24:13,960
Aaah!

411
00:24:14,007 --> 00:24:18,444
- [ Bone Snaps ]
-Ah, God! [ Groaning ]

412
00:24:18,527 --> 00:24:21,519
- You all right, son?
- Sir, yes, sir!

413
00:24:21,607 --> 00:24:24,644
It's my arm.
I reckon it's broken, sir.

414
00:24:24,687 --> 00:24:26,917
Medic!

415
00:24:26,967 --> 00:24:29,800
Pain is in your mind!

416
00:24:29,887 --> 00:24:32,526
- Who's next?
- [ Dizzy ] Sir.

417
00:24:32,567 --> 00:24:35,240
Recruit Flores
reporting for duty, sir.

418
00:24:44,007 --> 00:24:47,682
You specifically requested transfer from
Fort Cronkite to this training unit?

419
00:24:47,727 --> 00:24:51,197
- Sir, I heard it was the best, sir!
- It is the best.

420
00:24:52,367 --> 00:24:55,484
But what makes you think
you're good enough?

421
00:25:01,967 --> 00:25:03,958
Now, that's the kind of gal
who makes squad leader.

422
00:25:04,047 --> 00:25:06,277
That's my job
you're talking about.

423
00:25:07,567 --> 00:25:09,398
- Huh!
- Come on!

424
00:25:16,247 --> 00:25:18,397
[ Grunting ]

425
00:25:21,967 --> 00:25:24,037
[ Gasping ]

426
00:25:32,207 --> 00:25:34,038
You know, I'd like to kill
that Sergeant Zim.

427
00:25:34,127 --> 00:25:37,642
Whoa! Improper attitude! They'll
kick you out for talking like that.

428
00:25:37,687 --> 00:25:40,724
Bye-bye. There you go,
down Washout Lane.

429
00:25:40,807 --> 00:25:43,162
Yup. Either you got
what it takes or you don't.

430
00:25:43,247 --> 00:25:45,158
- Hey, there is a line!
- Wait your turn, Ace.

431
00:25:45,247 --> 00:25:48,842
Hey. At ease, little soldier.
It's all the same muck.

432
00:25:48,927 --> 00:25:50,565
Get in line like everyone else.

433
00:25:58,207 --> 00:26:02,598
[ Laughs ]
You got some guts for a rich kid.

434
00:26:02,687 --> 00:26:04,518
I guess you and me
could be buddies.

435
00:26:04,607 --> 00:26:06,563
What d'ya say?

436
00:26:06,607 --> 00:26:08,518
- I'm honoured.
- Hey!

437
00:26:08,567 --> 00:26:12,162
Of course you are!
Everybody should have a friend like me.

438
00:26:12,207 --> 00:26:15,677
- Come on, Ace!
Back of the line, man.
- Back, back, back, back!

439
00:26:15,767 --> 00:26:17,359
- What a jerk, man.
- Tough guy.

440
00:26:17,447 --> 00:26:19,438
Whoo.

441
00:26:19,487 --> 00:26:21,364
Hey, Rico.
Want to sit together?

442
00:26:21,407 --> 00:26:23,284
No, thanks, Diz.

443
00:26:24,647 --> 00:26:26,797
What's your malfunction, Rico?

444
00:26:28,007 --> 00:26:30,396
You are.

445
00:26:30,487 --> 00:26:34,036
I joined up to get out on my own,
and you had to tag along.

446
00:26:34,127 --> 00:26:37,005
You think I joined
the Mobile Infantry because of you?

447
00:26:37,047 --> 00:26:38,958
You saying you didn't?

448
00:26:44,447 --> 00:26:46,324
Hi.

449
00:26:46,367 --> 00:26:48,881
[ Rico ] Forget about it, Ace.
You don't stand a chance.

450
00:26:48,927 --> 00:26:51,521
What makes you even think you're going
to make squad leader, Rico?

451
00:26:51,607 --> 00:26:53,359
Something I've got you don't.

452
00:26:53,447 --> 00:26:56,166
- You rich kids are all the same.
- It isn't about that.

453
00:26:56,247 --> 00:26:58,317
- It's about who's the best.
- [ Dizzy ] Hey!

454
00:26:58,367 --> 00:27:00,323
[ Both Grunting ]

455
00:27:04,287 --> 00:27:06,164
[ Laughing ]

456
00:27:09,207 --> 00:27:11,038
[ Zim ]
First squad!

457
00:27:17,087 --> 00:27:19,760
Sir, I don't understand.

458
00:27:19,807 --> 00:27:22,275
Who needs a knife
in a nuke fight anyway?

459
00:27:22,327 --> 00:27:25,717
All you gotta do
is push a button. Sir.

460
00:27:25,807 --> 00:27:27,638
Cease fire!

461
00:27:28,807 --> 00:27:31,116
Put your hand
on that wall, Trooper!

462
00:27:33,367 --> 00:27:35,562
Put your hand on that wall!

463
00:27:41,407 --> 00:27:43,841
Aah!
[ Groaning ]

464
00:27:50,967 --> 00:27:55,199
The enemy cannot push a button
if you disable his hand.

465
00:27:57,927 --> 00:27:59,758
Medic!

466
00:28:00,807 --> 00:28:02,525
Hand me that towel, will ya?

467
00:28:02,607 --> 00:28:04,882
Ah, well. We all have
one thing in common.

468
00:28:04,927 --> 00:28:07,077
We were all stupid enough
to sign up for Mobile Infantry.

469
00:28:07,127 --> 00:28:09,004
Breckinridge, what's your excuse?

470
00:28:09,047 --> 00:28:11,515
My family's all farmers.
I hate farming.

471
00:28:11,607 --> 00:28:14,644
Mobile Infantry?
It's like pure picnic by comparison.

472
00:28:14,687 --> 00:28:17,963
All right, so they grow 'em big
and dumb on the farm planet, huh?

473
00:28:18,007 --> 00:28:20,362
- [ Man ] And pretty!
- [ Woman ] I like big.

474
00:28:20,407 --> 00:28:23,285
- Djana'd, what about you?
- Oh, I'm goin' in for politics.

475
00:28:23,327 --> 00:28:26,637
And, you know, you gotta be a citizen
for that, so here I am.

476
00:28:26,727 --> 00:28:29,366
- Ah, you want some responsibility.
- Yeah.

477
00:28:29,447 --> 00:28:31,597
Shujumi! C'mon.
Let's keep it going.

478
00:28:31,647 --> 00:28:34,241
I got into Harvard,
but my father says, "Forget it."

479
00:28:34,327 --> 00:28:36,966
It's gonna cost an arm
and a leg, you know?

480
00:28:37,047 --> 00:28:39,686
So, if I serve,
Federation pays my way! Ha-ha!

481
00:28:39,767 --> 00:28:44,283
I want to have babies. It's a lot easier
to get a licence if you serve, so--

482
00:28:44,367 --> 00:28:47,677
I'm going career.
Officer's training. All the way.

483
00:28:47,767 --> 00:28:50,998
Ah, future sky marshal.
All right, Rico, your turn.

484
00:28:52,407 --> 00:28:55,001
- Who asked you to be so nosy?
- What, I'm the bad guy?

485
00:28:55,087 --> 00:28:58,602
I'm gonna be a writer.
A writer's got a right to be nosy.

486
00:28:58,647 --> 00:29:01,366
Hey, Flores.
You know Rico from Buenos Aires.

487
00:29:01,447 --> 00:29:04,245
- What's his story?
- Oh, uh...

488
00:29:05,687 --> 00:29:07,757
he's here because of a girl.

489
00:29:07,847 --> 00:29:11,760
- [ Cheering, Catcalls ]
- Oh, Rico! Lover boy!

490
00:29:11,807 --> 00:29:14,082
[ Kitten ]
He's gettin'me excited!

491
00:29:14,167 --> 00:29:15,998
He's gonna blow!

492
00:29:18,647 --> 00:29:20,524
Is it you?

493
00:29:23,367 --> 00:29:28,725
[ Rico ] This is where we live.
Not much, but it's home.

494
00:29:28,807 --> 00:29:32,083
Right there, that's my bunk,
where I dream about you every night.

495
00:29:33,767 --> 00:29:37,965
Boot's pretty tough.
Sometimes, I think I won't make it.

496
00:29:38,007 --> 00:29:40,316
But then I think about
what you're doing, and I try harder.

497
00:29:40,407 --> 00:29:42,477
[ Hooting, Hollering ]

498
00:29:42,567 --> 00:29:44,683
- [ Farting Noise ]
- [ Rico ] Do you mind?

499
00:29:44,727 --> 00:29:47,002
We try harder, baby!
We try harder!

500
00:29:50,487 --> 00:29:53,559
Who knows? They might even
make me squad leader.

501
00:29:53,647 --> 00:29:57,162
- ** [ "Taps" ]
- Uh-oh. Well, I better pack it in.

502
00:29:57,207 --> 00:29:59,437
[ Screaming ]

503
00:29:59,527 --> 00:30:01,518
- Write me!
- * I love you Carmen *

504
00:30:01,567 --> 00:30:04,035
- I love you!
- I'm gonna kill you guys!

505
00:30:04,087 --> 00:30:06,123
* So much **

506
00:30:08,087 --> 00:30:09,998
Uhh. Bye!
Write me!

507
00:30:10,047 --> 00:30:11,685
[ Door Opening ]

508
00:30:11,767 --> 00:30:14,122
Orbit in five, Ibanez!

509
00:30:14,167 --> 00:30:16,362
First one there gets to fly.

510
00:30:18,327 --> 00:30:20,318
[ Both Giggling ]

511
00:30:30,607 --> 00:30:32,723
- Locking it down.
- [ Man ] Wait! Wait!

512
00:30:34,647 --> 00:30:37,207
Oh, no! Not Ibanez again!
She's crazy!

513
00:30:37,287 --> 00:30:39,437
Ready! Go!

514
00:30:45,487 --> 00:30:47,318
Yeah!

515
00:30:48,407 --> 00:30:50,284
Deploying wings.

516
00:31:32,327 --> 00:31:34,761
How come you're
in such a good mood? Huh?

517
00:31:34,807 --> 00:31:37,446
'Cause today I get to fly that.

518
00:31:58,327 --> 00:32:01,444
Pilot Trainee Ibanez
reporting for duty, ma'am.

519
00:32:01,527 --> 00:32:04,246
- Take the number two chair, Ibanez.
- Yes, ma'am.

520
00:32:08,727 --> 00:32:13,642
- Identify.
- Ibanez, T-3-2-5-A, clear.

521
00:32:16,647 --> 00:32:20,356
[ Laughs ]
What are you doing here?

522
00:32:21,607 --> 00:32:24,405
I'm the guy who's gonna teach you
to fly this crate.

523
00:32:24,447 --> 00:32:26,961
Ah. Assistant instructor.

524
00:32:27,047 --> 00:32:29,845
Should I call you "sir"?

525
00:32:29,887 --> 00:32:32,401
Only when I give you an order.

526
00:32:32,487 --> 00:32:34,364
Prepare for departure.

527
00:32:34,447 --> 00:32:39,441
It's amazing, us running into each other
like this. Maybe it's fate.

528
00:32:39,487 --> 00:32:44,561
Maybe not. I heard about this crazy girl
coming through the Academy.

529
00:32:44,607 --> 00:32:49,203
Solid math, a little wild
on the stick but a natural.

530
00:32:49,287 --> 00:32:52,962
When it turned out to be you,
I just made sure that
we would run into each other.

531
00:32:53,047 --> 00:32:55,242
[ Woman On P.A. ] Rodger Young,
cleared for undocking and departure.

532
00:32:55,287 --> 00:32:57,517
All right, Ibanez.
Take her out.

533
00:32:57,567 --> 00:33:00,081
Yes, ma'am.

534
00:33:00,167 --> 00:33:02,158
[ P.A. ]
All systems go.

535
00:33:04,367 --> 00:33:06,198
[ Engines Roaring ]

536
00:33:25,047 --> 00:33:28,517
In simulation,
my supervisors could never keep up.

537
00:33:28,567 --> 00:33:33,038
Well, this isn't simulation any more,
so take her out easy, Cadet.

538
00:33:33,087 --> 00:33:34,440
Yes, sir.

539
00:33:42,407 --> 00:33:44,557
[ Computer ]
Five metres from object.

540
00:33:47,127 --> 00:33:49,118
Three metres from object.

541
00:33:53,047 --> 00:33:55,322
Clear.

542
00:33:56,807 --> 00:34:01,198
- Don't exceed port speed.
- Or what?

543
00:34:01,287 --> 00:34:05,200
Or they revoke
your flight status... and mine.

544
00:34:06,647 --> 00:34:09,207
Your career is in my hands.

545
00:34:15,967 --> 00:34:18,435
Steady as she goes, Number Two.
Prepare for warp.

546
00:34:18,487 --> 00:34:22,639
- Yes, ma'am.
- Number One, design for Jupiter orbit.

547
00:34:22,727 --> 00:34:26,322
[ Man On P.A. ] All crew, all sections.
Stand by to cut in C-drive--

548
00:34:26,407 --> 00:34:28,238
[ Zander ]
Stellar drive in...

549
00:34:28,327 --> 00:34:30,158
- five, four...
- five, four...

550
00:34:30,247 --> 00:34:33,125
- ready, steady, go!
- three, two, one.

551
00:34:44,047 --> 00:34:45,878
[ Grunting ]

552
00:34:45,967 --> 00:34:47,798
Aah!

553
00:34:57,087 --> 00:34:58,964
I'm goin' in! Move!

554
00:35:07,127 --> 00:35:08,958
Man, they're defended!
No way in!

555
00:35:09,047 --> 00:35:11,117
[ Laughing, Hooting ]

556
00:35:11,207 --> 00:35:13,118
- Flip six, three hole.
- What?

557
00:35:13,207 --> 00:35:15,880
We run a flip six, three hole play,
and you can score.

558
00:35:15,927 --> 00:35:17,679
- Cover me!
- You got it.

559
00:35:25,527 --> 00:35:27,404
Now!

560
00:35:33,687 --> 00:35:36,076
- Thanks, buddy!
- Bastard!

561
00:35:44,807 --> 00:35:46,638
Yeah!

562
00:35:51,447 --> 00:35:53,438
The kid's got some moves.

563
00:35:53,527 --> 00:35:55,643
Give him a squad.
See what he can do.

564
00:35:57,327 --> 00:35:59,921
[ Cadets Laughing, Chattering ]

565
00:36:00,007 --> 00:36:01,838
[ Pool Balls Clattering ]

566
00:36:01,927 --> 00:36:05,442
Someone's got to teach you guys
how to play some pool here.

567
00:36:05,527 --> 00:36:09,566
Look at him. You ever seen anybody
so pleased with himself?

568
00:36:09,647 --> 00:36:13,322
Well, Zim must've had to choose someone
to be his brown-nose.

569
00:36:18,567 --> 00:36:20,956
I couldn't have done it
without you, Diz.

570
00:36:22,687 --> 00:36:24,564
Friends?

571
00:36:26,207 --> 00:36:28,084
Friends.

572
00:36:29,047 --> 00:36:30,844
[ Bronski ]
Mail call! Levy!

573
00:36:30,927 --> 00:36:32,838
- Yeah, that's me.
- Shujumi!

574
00:36:32,887 --> 00:36:34,764
- Here.
- Rico.

575
00:36:34,807 --> 00:36:36,684
- Here.
- Breckinridge.

576
00:36:36,727 --> 00:36:38,922
- Nyla.
- Yeah, here I am.

577
00:36:38,967 --> 00:36:40,844
[ Nyla ]
Oh, great. My dad.

578
00:36:40,887 --> 00:36:42,878
[ Bronski ]
That's all, folks.

579
00:36:49,807 --> 00:36:53,959
Hi,Johnny. I'm sorry I haven't
written you sooner, but--

580
00:36:54,007 --> 00:36:57,204
- Oh, Rico! You don't
deserve that! Ho, ho!
- Shh!

581
00:36:57,247 --> 00:37:00,876
They've really got us going. They must
have made you squad leader by now.

582
00:37:00,927 --> 00:37:03,441
And if they haven't,
tell 'em to talk to me.

583
00:37:03,527 --> 00:37:06,485
See? All it takes
is the love of a good woman.

584
00:37:06,527 --> 00:37:08,006
Now, that is a woman!

585
00:37:08,087 --> 00:37:12,080
Look at that.
Isn't it beautiful?

586
00:37:12,167 --> 00:37:13,998
I love it out here.

587
00:37:16,287 --> 00:37:20,439
[ Sighs ] That's also
the problem, because...

588
00:37:21,767 --> 00:37:23,598
I think I'm gonna go career.

589
00:37:25,087 --> 00:37:28,318
I want a command,
a ship of my own and, you know...

590
00:37:30,647 --> 00:37:34,162
I don't think that's gonna leave
a lot of room for you and me,Johnny.

591
00:37:37,407 --> 00:37:40,240
I know that's not
what you wanted to hear...

592
00:37:40,287 --> 00:37:42,164
but, uh...

593
00:37:44,247 --> 00:37:46,602
I have to follow my heart.

594
00:37:46,647 --> 00:37:48,524
I'm sorry.

595
00:37:50,367 --> 00:37:52,085
Write me. All right?

596
00:37:53,487 --> 00:37:56,365
Write me, so that I'll know
we'll always be friends.

597
00:38:11,607 --> 00:38:13,484
[ Sighs ]

598
00:38:13,527 --> 00:38:16,724
Funny how they always want to be friends
after they rip your guts out, huh?

599
00:38:17,727 --> 00:38:20,560
Yeah.
Well, that's what I deserve.

600
00:38:21,847 --> 00:38:23,678
What are you talkin' about?

601
00:38:26,007 --> 00:38:30,717
I joined up for her. I wouldn't
even be here if it wasn't for her.

602
00:38:30,807 --> 00:38:33,799
What are you talkin' about?
You made squad leader on your own.

603
00:38:35,927 --> 00:38:38,885
And, hey, you still got me
to kick around.

604
00:38:42,687 --> 00:38:44,564
[ Zim ]
Fun and games are over, children!

605
00:38:44,607 --> 00:38:48,725
You will be firing live ammunition
in a simulated combat environment.

606
00:38:48,767 --> 00:38:53,045
You will exercise extreme caution
on my assault course!

607
00:38:53,127 --> 00:38:55,766
- Do you get me?
- Sir, yes, sir!

608
00:38:55,847 --> 00:38:58,839
Rico, take 'em out.

609
00:38:58,927 --> 00:39:02,442
First fire team with me.
Next team in ten seconds!

610
00:39:02,487 --> 00:39:06,958
Maximum score has been 2 80.
I expect you to do better.

611
00:39:07,047 --> 00:39:08,799
- [ Buzzer Sounds ]
- Go!

612
00:39:08,887 --> 00:39:10,718
[ All Yelling ]

613
00:39:10,807 --> 00:39:12,798
[ Rico ]
Stay low! Keep moving!

614
00:39:16,567 --> 00:39:18,319
[ Rico ]
Shujumi, stay down!

615
00:39:26,927 --> 00:39:30,158
Hey! Goddamn it, Breckinridge!
Clear my line of fire!

616
00:39:30,247 --> 00:39:32,238
It's my helmet.
It's all screwed up.

617
00:39:32,287 --> 00:39:34,164
- You're gonna blow the score!
- Man!

618
00:39:34,247 --> 00:39:37,045
- Dumb shit!
- Diz, stay put! What's the problem?

619
00:39:37,127 --> 00:39:39,083
Damn thing keeps getting in my way!

620
00:39:39,127 --> 00:39:41,004
How come whenever
something goes wrong,
it's always you, Breckinridge?

621
00:39:41,047 --> 00:39:43,607
- It must be 'cause I'm big and dumb!
- Yeah, right!

622
00:39:43,647 --> 00:39:45,683
Ohh!

623
00:39:49,687 --> 00:39:51,723
Medic!

624
00:39:54,247 --> 00:39:57,922
[ Zim ] Rico! You are relieved
of squad command!

625
00:39:59,847 --> 00:40:02,759
[ Man ] Rico, did you give the recruit
permission to remove his helmet?

626
00:40:02,807 --> 00:40:07,198
Sir, yes, sir. Breckinridge
reported a helmet malfunction,
and I asked him to show me, sir.

627
00:40:07,287 --> 00:40:10,962
Are you rated to repair
the M-3 tactical helmet, Rico?

628
00:40:12,087 --> 00:40:13,918
Sir, no, sir!

629
00:40:14,007 --> 00:40:18,444
Then why did you order your man
to remove his helmet
during a live fire exercise?

630
00:40:18,487 --> 00:40:22,844
Sir, I needed everyone
in my squad operational, sir!

631
00:40:22,927 --> 00:40:25,441
I wanted to win, sir!

632
00:40:39,447 --> 00:40:43,918
[ C.O. ] Sergeant, we've already lost
two recruits over this incident.

633
00:40:43,967 --> 00:40:46,800
Think there's any possibility
of salvaging this man?

634
00:40:48,647 --> 00:40:51,115
Yes, sir, I do.

635
00:40:51,207 --> 00:40:53,846
All right.

636
00:40:53,887 --> 00:40:55,878
We'll try administrative punishment.

637
00:41:01,367 --> 00:41:03,244
Prisoner, halt!

638
00:41:19,847 --> 00:41:21,678
Bite down on this, son.

639
00:41:21,727 --> 00:41:25,766
It helps. I know.

640
00:41:34,487 --> 00:41:37,524
[ C.O. On P.A. ]
For incompetence of command...

641
00:41:37,567 --> 00:41:42,118
for failure to abide
by safety regulations
during a live fire exercise...

642
00:41:43,527 --> 00:41:47,759
for negligence which contributed
to the death of a teammate...

643
00:41:47,807 --> 00:41:51,766
Recruit TraineeJohn Rico is sentenced
to administrative punishment.

644
00:41:53,007 --> 00:41:54,838
Ten lashes.

645
00:41:55,767 --> 00:41:57,962
You may carry out the sentence.

646
00:42:04,847 --> 00:42:06,883
[ Bronski ]
One!

647
00:42:08,327 --> 00:42:10,318
- Two!
- [ Muffled Groans ]

648
00:42:11,967 --> 00:42:14,640
Three!

649
00:42:14,727 --> 00:42:17,161
Four!

650
00:42:18,407 --> 00:42:20,557
Five!

651
00:42:22,807 --> 00:42:24,684
- Six!
- [ Groaning ]

652
00:42:25,607 --> 00:42:27,438
Seven!

653
00:42:28,807 --> 00:42:31,275
- [ Whip Cracks ]
- Eight!

654
00:42:31,327 --> 00:42:33,204
- [ Whip Cracks ]
- Nine!

655
00:42:34,207 --> 00:42:36,084
- [ Whip Cracks ]
- Ten!

656
00:42:47,287 --> 00:42:51,405
[ Man ] All sections secure. EBX is
high-normal. Switch to slave on my mark.

657
00:42:51,447 --> 00:42:53,517
- Mark.
- [ Sighs ]

658
00:42:56,207 --> 00:42:59,119
[ Chuckles ]
Thanks. You read my mind.

659
00:43:00,447 --> 00:43:03,439
Oh, third watch
always seems to last forever.

660
00:43:03,527 --> 00:43:07,679
I don't know. Depends on who
you're spending it with.

661
00:43:10,007 --> 00:43:11,759
Something's wrong.

662
00:43:15,767 --> 00:43:17,997
- There!
- No.

663
00:43:18,047 --> 00:43:21,676
I replotted the course.
It's more efficient this way.

664
00:43:21,767 --> 00:43:24,486
Three weeks aboard a starship
and you think you can lick my navs?

665
00:43:24,567 --> 00:43:26,876
[ Laughs ]
Check it.

666
00:43:31,687 --> 00:43:36,203
You know, I was talking with
Captain Deladier and, uh, she said--

667
00:43:36,247 --> 00:43:40,081
Don't change the subject.
Am I right?

668
00:43:46,007 --> 00:43:50,000
[ Sighs ]
Yeah. Yeah. You're right.

669
00:43:50,087 --> 00:43:52,396
So, what did the captain say?

670
00:43:53,647 --> 00:43:56,878
She thinks we should
team up officially...

671
00:43:58,087 --> 00:44:01,079
and crew for her.

672
00:44:01,167 --> 00:44:04,398
- You and me, huh?
- We're good together, Carmen.

673
00:44:04,487 --> 00:44:07,718
We're way ahead of the curve
in every department.

674
00:44:07,767 --> 00:44:10,759
I can anticipate you.

675
00:44:10,807 --> 00:44:13,480
You know what I want.

676
00:44:14,647 --> 00:44:18,435
No. What do you want?

677
00:44:20,007 --> 00:44:21,838
[ Low Rumbling ]

678
00:44:25,607 --> 00:44:28,326
There's a gravity field out there.

679
00:44:29,847 --> 00:44:32,520
- Run a scan. Sensors on.
- There.

680
00:44:34,007 --> 00:44:37,443
- [ Carmen ]
Gravity at 2-2-5 and rising.
- Report!

681
00:44:37,527 --> 00:44:40,963
Captain, we are in the path
of an unidentified object
moving toward us at high speed.

682
00:44:41,047 --> 00:44:44,244
Profile suggests
an asteroid, ma'am.

683
00:44:54,327 --> 00:44:56,397
- [ Computer Beeping ]
- [ Zander ] Impact.:six seconds!

684
00:44:56,487 --> 00:44:58,637
Emergency evasion!

685
00:45:02,567 --> 00:45:04,205
Three...

686
00:45:04,247 --> 00:45:06,966
two...

687
00:45:07,927 --> 00:45:09,280
fire!

688
00:45:23,447 --> 00:45:25,199
Close compartment 21!

689
00:45:38,367 --> 00:45:40,244
Where'd it come from?

690
00:45:40,287 --> 00:45:42,960
It came out of the
Arachnid Quarantine Zone, ma'am.

691
00:45:44,767 --> 00:45:47,565
Number Four, contact Fleet.
Tell them there's a loose
asteroid headed their way.

692
00:45:47,607 --> 00:45:49,757
Communications are down, ma'am.
They're gone.

693
00:45:51,207 --> 00:45:53,675
- Damage assessment!
- Hull's compromised.

694
00:45:53,767 --> 00:45:55,598
We're lucky to be alive, ma'am.

695
00:45:55,687 --> 00:45:58,360
Luck didn't have anything
to do with it.

696
00:45:58,447 --> 00:46:00,642
We have a hell of a flight team.

697
00:46:13,207 --> 00:46:15,038
[ Sighs ]

698
00:46:15,127 --> 00:46:17,436
It really stinks, you goin'.

699
00:46:17,527 --> 00:46:20,803
Yeah, well, the Mobile Infantry'll
just have to get along without me.

700
00:46:20,887 --> 00:46:22,718
[ Bag Zips ]

701
00:46:24,247 --> 00:46:26,078
I don't get it, Rico.

702
00:46:26,167 --> 00:46:29,443
You took your licks. If they didn't
want you, they would've kicked you out.

703
00:46:29,527 --> 00:46:31,358
Hey!

704
00:46:31,447 --> 00:46:33,756
I joined up for the wrong reasons.
I got a guy killed.

705
00:46:33,847 --> 00:46:36,645
I figure that kinda proves
I don't have what it takes.

706
00:46:36,727 --> 00:46:39,525
Rico, your call's goin' through.

707
00:46:39,607 --> 00:46:41,438
Take it there.

708
00:46:46,967 --> 00:46:48,559
Hello?

709
00:46:48,647 --> 00:46:50,478
Oh,Johnny!

710
00:46:50,567 --> 00:46:53,445
- Hi, Mom.
- B-Bill, pick it up. It's Johnny.

711
00:46:53,527 --> 00:46:55,040
-Johnny?
- Dad.

712
00:46:55,127 --> 00:46:56,560
- Where's your uniform?
- Bill!

713
00:46:58,167 --> 00:47:01,477
It's just good to hear from you.
How are you, son?

714
00:47:01,527 --> 00:47:04,678
It's not really
working out here for me, Dad.

715
00:47:04,727 --> 00:47:08,083
I was thinking-- I was hoping
it would be all right if I came home.

716
00:47:08,127 --> 00:47:11,119
Well, of c-- of course.
You should come home immediately.

717
00:47:12,327 --> 00:47:14,397
I'm sorry.
I've been an idiot.

718
00:47:14,487 --> 00:47:16,876
Don't talk like that.
Just come on home.

719
00:47:16,927 --> 00:47:19,043
We'll talk things out.

720
00:47:19,127 --> 00:47:20,958
We love you, son.

721
00:47:22,247 --> 00:47:24,556
- My, what's that?
- Looks like rain.

722
00:47:24,647 --> 00:47:27,559
- This time of the year?
- Sure is dark--

723
00:47:27,607 --> 00:47:31,361
Your transmission has been terminated
due to atmospheric interference.

724
00:47:31,447 --> 00:47:33,278
Please try your call again later.

725
00:47:38,967 --> 00:47:40,798
I'll see ya.

726
00:47:40,887 --> 00:47:42,718
Hey.

727
00:47:42,807 --> 00:47:46,322
You take that stroll down Washout Lane,
you're only proving one thing.

728
00:47:46,407 --> 00:47:48,716
What's that, Diz?

729
00:47:50,887 --> 00:47:53,685
That you don't have what it takes
to be a citizen.

730
00:47:59,367 --> 00:48:01,835
[ Shouting ]

731
00:48:01,927 --> 00:48:04,282
- * Sound off *
- * Stand by *

732
00:48:04,367 --> 00:48:06,278
- * Sound off *
- * Stand by *

733
00:48:06,327 --> 00:48:09,637
[ Shouting, Singing Continues ]

734
00:48:10,847 --> 00:48:14,396
Stand by!
Left, right, left!

735
00:48:14,487 --> 00:48:17,285
[ Shouting Intensifies ]

736
00:48:20,607 --> 00:48:22,837
Hold it!
What's happening?

737
00:48:22,927 --> 00:48:24,758
Bombed!

738
00:48:24,847 --> 00:48:26,678
Lost the whole city!

739
00:48:27,807 --> 00:48:29,763
Hey, what's goin' on?

740
00:48:29,847 --> 00:48:32,566
Wh-What's going on?
Hey, Kitten, what's goin' on?

741
00:48:32,607 --> 00:48:35,121
War! We're goin' to war!

742
00:48:39,047 --> 00:48:42,801
[ Narrator ] The devastation
we are seeing is unparalleled.

743
00:48:42,847 --> 00:48:46,556
Judging from early estimates,
millions dead, a city in ruins.

744
00:48:46,647 --> 00:48:49,445
Is that Geneva?

745
00:48:49,527 --> 00:48:51,438
Goddamn bugs whacked us,Johnny.

746
00:48:51,527 --> 00:48:54,803
[ Narrator ] The meteor was shot
out of orbit by Bug plasma...

747
00:48:54,887 --> 00:48:58,163
that derived from Klendathu,
the Arachnid's home planet.

748
00:49:04,567 --> 00:49:06,797
Nothing lives
in what was once called...

749
00:49:06,887 --> 00:49:09,276
the Latin paradise.

750
00:49:09,367 --> 00:49:11,198
Oh,Johnny, that's us.

751
00:49:11,287 --> 00:49:14,757
[ Narrator ] Buenos Aires
has been wiped off the Earth.

752
00:49:18,407 --> 00:49:20,841
It's home.

753
00:49:23,127 --> 00:49:26,756
[ Narrator ] The Federal Council
met moments ago and voted unanimously...

754
00:49:26,807 --> 00:49:29,799
for mobilization to destroy
the Arachnid threat.

755
00:49:36,287 --> 00:49:38,721
- I'm serious. I'll go anywhere.
- Forget it, Zim. We need you here.

756
00:49:38,807 --> 00:49:40,638
I want combat, sir!

757
00:49:40,727 --> 00:49:43,878
The only way you're gonna see
combat is if you bust yourself
to private. Get me?

758
00:49:43,927 --> 00:49:46,077
Yes, sir. I get you.

759
00:49:46,167 --> 00:49:49,204
- Sir!
- What do you want, Rico?

760
00:49:49,247 --> 00:49:54,275
-I wish to reconsider
my request to drop out, sir.
-You already signed your 1240-A.

761
00:49:54,327 --> 00:49:57,637
- It wouldn't be legal.
- Major, I know it was wrong.

762
00:49:57,687 --> 00:50:00,565
I didn't learn from one mistake,
and I made another, sir.

763
00:50:00,647 --> 00:50:02,478
You made your decision, son.

764
00:50:02,567 --> 00:50:06,879
Sir, my family-- my whole family
was in Buenos Aires, sir.

765
00:50:09,807 --> 00:50:11,638
Is this your signature, Rico?

766
00:50:12,727 --> 00:50:14,604
Sir, yes, it is, sir!

767
00:50:18,967 --> 00:50:21,686
Doesn't look like it to me.

768
00:50:24,247 --> 00:50:26,477
Carry on, Private.

769
00:50:26,527 --> 00:50:28,324
Yes, sir!

770
00:50:39,566 --> 00:50:41,716
[ Narrator ]
Out of the ashes of Buenos Aires...

771
00:50:41,806 --> 00:50:44,479
comes first sorrow...

772
00:50:44,566 --> 00:50:46,284
then anger.

773
00:50:46,326 --> 00:50:48,681
The only good Bug
is a dead Bug.

774
00:50:48,726 --> 00:50:52,036
In Geneva,
the Federal Council convenes.

775
00:50:52,086 --> 00:50:55,601
We must meet the threat
with our valour, our blood...

776
00:50:55,646 --> 00:50:57,921
indeed, with our very lives...

777
00:50:58,006 --> 00:51:00,804
to ensure
that human civilization...

778
00:51:00,886 --> 00:51:02,717
not insect...

779
00:51:02,806 --> 00:51:05,366
dominates this galaxy
now and always.

780
00:51:05,446 --> 00:51:07,277
[ Applause ]

781
00:51:07,406 --> 00:51:11,240
Sky Marshal Dienes announces plans
for an offensive against Klendathu...

782
00:51:11,326 --> 00:51:14,124
the source of the Bug meteor
that destroyed Buenos Aires.

783
00:51:16,686 --> 00:51:20,235
Every day Federal scientists
are looking for new ways to kill Bugs.

784
00:51:20,286 --> 00:51:24,837
Your basic Arachnid warrior isn't too
smart, but you can blow off a limb...

785
00:51:24,926 --> 00:51:27,315
[ Screeching ]

786
00:51:27,406 --> 00:51:29,715
and it's still
86% combat effective.

787
00:51:29,806 --> 00:51:33,719
Here's a tip: Aim for the nerve stem
and put it down for good.

788
00:51:39,926 --> 00:51:43,157
[ Narrator ]
Everyone's doing their part. Are you?

789
00:51:43,246 --> 00:51:45,555
- Aah! Aah! Aah!
- Die! Die!

790
00:51:45,606 --> 00:51:47,881
The war effort
needs your effort...

791
00:51:47,966 --> 00:51:49,877
at work, at home,
in your community.

792
00:51:52,926 --> 00:51:55,235
We now break net
and take you live...

793
00:51:55,326 --> 00:51:57,556
to Fleet battle station Ticonderoga...

794
00:51:57,646 --> 00:51:59,637
deep inside
the Arachnid Quarantine Zone...

795
00:51:59,686 --> 00:52:02,803
where the men and women
of the Federal Armed Services...

796
00:52:02,846 --> 00:52:04,723
prepare to attack.

797
00:52:04,766 --> 00:52:08,042
[ Man ] D-X-Q uplink
on two, one. You're on.

798
00:52:08,126 --> 00:52:12,642
No one here in the A.Q.Z.
knows exactly when the invasion
of Klendathu will occur...

799
00:52:12,726 --> 00:52:14,557
but everyone's
talking about it...

800
00:52:14,646 --> 00:52:16,477
and the talk says tomorrow.

801
00:52:16,566 --> 00:52:18,875
Here's a bunch of M.I. kids that
look like they could eat Bugs for lunch.

802
00:52:18,966 --> 00:52:20,797
[ Chuckles ]
Yum-yum-yum.

803
00:52:20,886 --> 00:52:23,684
So, Trooper, you're not too worried
about fighting the Arachnids?

804
00:52:23,766 --> 00:52:26,564
Hey, shoot a nuke down a Bug hole,
you got a lot of dead bugs.

805
00:52:26,646 --> 00:52:29,444
I just hope it's not over
before we get some.

806
00:52:29,526 --> 00:52:33,280
Some say the Bugs were provoked
by the intrusion of humans
into their natural habitat...

807
00:52:33,366 --> 00:52:37,120
that a live-and-let-live policy
is preferable to war with the bugs--

808
00:52:37,206 --> 00:52:40,960
Let me tell you somethin'. I'm from
Buenos Aires, and I say kill 'em all.

809
00:52:41,046 --> 00:52:43,480
- Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!
- Oh, yeah!

810
00:52:43,526 --> 00:52:45,403
Big, bad Bugs, huh?

811
00:52:45,446 --> 00:52:47,243
Hey, guys,
we oughta get tattoos.

812
00:52:47,326 --> 00:52:50,124
- Let's all get cut together.
- What do I want a tattoo for?

813
00:52:50,206 --> 00:52:53,164
- What, your skin's too pretty?
- Hey, Johnny!

814
00:52:55,286 --> 00:52:57,117
Johnny Rico!

815
00:52:58,646 --> 00:53:00,477
Carmen?

816
00:53:01,846 --> 00:53:04,121
- Oh.
- Oh.

817
00:53:04,206 --> 00:53:08,245
At ease. Guess I oughta
lose the hat when I'm off duty.

818
00:53:08,286 --> 00:53:10,436
Hi, Diz.

819
00:53:10,526 --> 00:53:12,437
Carmen.

820
00:53:14,246 --> 00:53:16,601
My mother was right about you.

821
00:53:16,646 --> 00:53:19,001
You look great in a uniform.

822
00:53:19,046 --> 00:53:20,923
You look pretty good yourself.

823
00:53:22,526 --> 00:53:24,357
So, what do you hear?

824
00:53:24,446 --> 00:53:26,755
You know about anyone
who made it out of B.A. alive?

825
00:53:26,846 --> 00:53:29,644
Most of the time,
I don't think about it...

826
00:53:29,726 --> 00:53:31,603
like it happened
to someone else.

827
00:53:31,646 --> 00:53:35,275
Then it hits me,
and I can't stop crying.

828
00:53:35,326 --> 00:53:38,523
Well, we're still alive.
Gotta be happy about that.

829
00:53:38,566 --> 00:53:41,399
You don't look very happy
to see me.

830
00:53:42,686 --> 00:53:44,881
Should I be?

831
00:53:44,926 --> 00:53:48,202
Johnny.
It's different now.

832
00:53:48,286 --> 00:53:53,485
We're at war. I think what I did was
probably the best thing for both of us.

833
00:53:53,566 --> 00:53:55,397
Everything copacetic, Lieutenant?

834
00:53:56,646 --> 00:53:58,762
Zander, you remember Johnny.

835
00:53:58,846 --> 00:54:01,155
Zander and I are a flight team now.

836
00:54:01,246 --> 00:54:03,157
Yeah. Best in the fleet.

837
00:54:04,166 --> 00:54:06,043
I get it.

838
00:54:06,086 --> 00:54:08,281
This is the part
that's best for both of us.

839
00:54:08,326 --> 00:54:10,635
Don't do me any more favours.

840
00:54:10,686 --> 00:54:13,564
-Johnny, wait--
- Forget it, Lieutenant.
He's Mobile Infantry.

841
00:54:13,646 --> 00:54:15,477
See, when you're
trained to kill...

842
00:54:15,566 --> 00:54:17,955
it just doesn't pay
to be polite.

843
00:54:18,046 --> 00:54:21,083
You got something to say
about the Mobile Infantry?

844
00:54:21,166 --> 00:54:22,997
I think you heard me.

845
00:54:23,086 --> 00:54:26,123
You wanna make something
of it... Private?

846
00:54:27,646 --> 00:54:29,477
Not with an officer, no, sir.

847
00:54:29,566 --> 00:54:31,602
The M.I. doesn't admit
stupid troopers.

848
00:54:31,646 --> 00:54:34,604
- Well, let's disregard rank.
- Zander, please.

849
00:54:34,686 --> 00:54:36,517
[ Trooper ]
You go, Rico.

850
00:54:36,606 --> 00:54:39,245
Everybody hear that?
Rank is not an issue here!

851
00:54:39,326 --> 00:54:42,284
- Don't do this.
- Come on. What's he gonna do?

852
00:54:42,366 --> 00:54:44,436
[ Crowd Shouting ]

853
00:54:48,446 --> 00:54:52,041
[ Groaning ]
Aaah!

854
00:54:55,526 --> 00:54:57,994
Come on!
Jarheads!

855
00:54:58,046 --> 00:54:59,798
Come on!
I'm gonna kill you!

856
00:55:01,286 --> 00:55:04,278
I'm gonna kill you!
I'll kill you!

857
00:55:04,326 --> 00:55:06,635
-Johnny, don't! Quit it!
- Come on!

858
00:55:06,686 --> 00:55:09,883
He's not worth it!
Come on! Come on!

859
00:55:09,926 --> 00:55:13,635
Forget it, Rico! Mobile Infantry
and Fleet don't mix. Come on.

860
00:55:15,486 --> 00:55:17,317
Come on. Let's go.

861
00:55:18,806 --> 00:55:20,637
Jarheads.

862
00:55:22,286 --> 00:55:24,595
- [ Kitten ] Whoo-hoo!
- [ Ace ] Mobile Infantry rules!

863
00:55:24,686 --> 00:55:27,723
- Yeah!
- Oh, God, that hurts!

864
00:55:27,806 --> 00:55:30,923
Hey, well, I got somethin' that might
hurt just a little bit more, buddy.

865
00:55:31,006 --> 00:55:32,837
- Aaah!
- Ohh!
- [ Laughs ]

866
00:55:32,926 --> 00:55:35,724
Oh, yeah!
We're gonna fight, and we're gonna win!

867
00:55:35,806 --> 00:55:39,082
[ All Yelling, Hooting ]

868
00:55:52,726 --> 00:55:54,557
This is the captain speaking.

869
00:55:54,646 --> 00:55:56,523
All personnel
prepare for drop.

870
00:55:56,606 --> 00:55:59,404
We are at "T"minus three
and counting.

871
00:56:09,966 --> 00:56:12,764
We are going in
with the first wave.

872
00:56:12,846 --> 00:56:14,996
Means more Bugs
for us to kill.

873
00:56:15,086 --> 00:56:19,443
You smash the entire area!
You kill anything that has more
than two legs! You get me?

874
00:56:19,486 --> 00:56:21,158
We get you, sir!

875
00:57:06,446 --> 00:57:09,882
- Plasma, ma'am, from the planet.
- Bug batteries.

876
00:57:09,926 --> 00:57:12,838
According to Military Intelligence,
it'll be random and light.

877
00:57:14,246 --> 00:57:18,683
- Drop status?
- Drop is... 35 percent complete, ma'am.

878
00:57:24,166 --> 00:57:26,600
Steady as she goes, Number Two.

879
00:57:33,606 --> 00:57:35,756
[ Groaning ]

880
00:57:35,806 --> 00:57:37,683
[ Exhales ]

881
00:57:37,726 --> 00:57:39,603
Remember your training...

882
00:57:39,646 --> 00:57:42,114
and you will
make it back alive!

883
00:57:45,006 --> 00:57:46,837
[ Retching ]

884
00:57:46,926 --> 00:57:49,201
[ Exhaling ]

885
00:57:49,246 --> 00:57:51,635
Whoooo-hoo!

886
00:57:59,006 --> 00:58:01,804
This isn't random or light.
Someone made a mistake.

887
00:58:01,886 --> 00:58:04,764
That's it.
We're empty, ma'am.

888
00:58:13,406 --> 00:58:15,237
Someone made
a big goddamn mistake!

889
00:58:22,046 --> 00:58:24,765
Break for high orbit!

890
00:58:40,166 --> 00:58:41,997
[ Grunts ]
Aaah!

891
00:58:58,166 --> 00:59:00,396
[ Shouting ]

892
00:59:00,446 --> 00:59:02,437
Go! Go! Go!

893
00:59:07,326 --> 00:59:09,635
Fall in!

894
00:59:28,726 --> 00:59:30,523
Rockets up!

895
00:59:30,566 --> 00:59:32,443
Rocket crew, move up!

896
00:59:55,046 --> 00:59:57,958
- Nuke 'em! Levy! Rico!
- Heat 'em up!

897
01:00:02,406 --> 01:00:05,204
- Set.
- Fire!

898
01:00:11,006 --> 01:00:13,884
- Follow me!
- Let's go!

899
01:00:13,926 --> 01:00:16,440
- [ Shouting Continues ]
- [ Gunfire ]

900
01:00:16,486 --> 01:00:19,478
First Platoon, left flank!

901
01:00:19,526 --> 01:00:21,881
Spread out!

902
01:00:21,966 --> 01:00:23,797
First and second squads,
follow me!

903
01:00:23,886 --> 01:00:26,525
Shoot cover!
Left, with me!

904
01:00:26,566 --> 01:00:29,080
[ Shouting Continues ]

905
01:00:29,166 --> 01:00:30,997
[ Screeching ]

906
01:00:31,086 --> 01:00:32,917
Fire!

907
01:00:35,486 --> 01:00:37,317
Aaaah!

908
01:00:38,446 --> 01:00:40,277
[ Screaming Continues ]

909
01:00:47,806 --> 01:00:49,478
[ Screeching Continues ]

910
01:00:49,566 --> 01:00:51,397
Here they come!

911
01:00:54,446 --> 01:00:57,006
- Ace, what are we doing?
- Uh, I-I don't know.

912
01:01:01,606 --> 01:01:03,881
I don't know.

913
01:01:03,966 --> 01:01:06,036
Kill them!
Kill them all!

914
01:01:11,566 --> 01:01:13,079
Come on!

915
01:01:15,646 --> 01:01:18,843
Come on! Come on!
You want some?

916
01:01:18,926 --> 01:01:21,679
Here's some! Yeah!

917
01:01:21,726 --> 01:01:23,603
Here's some of this!

918
01:01:23,646 --> 01:01:26,319
[ Screaming ]

919
01:01:27,326 --> 01:01:30,796
- Oh, my God!
- Shujumi!

920
01:01:30,846 --> 01:01:32,882
No! No! No!

921
01:01:33,926 --> 01:01:36,042
[ Screaming Continues ]
Help!

922
01:01:36,126 --> 01:01:38,003
Help! Get it off!

923
01:01:38,046 --> 01:01:41,243
No! God!

924
01:01:46,286 --> 01:01:48,436
Let's get out of here!

925
01:01:50,886 --> 01:01:53,559
Fall back!

926
01:01:53,606 --> 01:01:56,074
[ Whimpering ]

927
01:01:56,126 --> 01:01:58,594
[ Screaming, Groaning ]

928
01:02:00,366 --> 01:02:02,197
[ Screeching ]

929
01:02:16,486 --> 01:02:20,274
- [ On Radio ] Retreat!
All units, prep for retrieval!
- What's goin' on?

930
01:02:20,326 --> 01:02:22,681
- Repeat! All units,
all battle stations!
- You got some?

931
01:02:22,726 --> 01:02:27,242
- It's a general retreat!
Back to the boats!
- Come on! Let's go!

932
01:02:27,326 --> 01:02:29,157
[ Shouting ]

933
01:02:29,246 --> 01:02:32,602
[ Correspondent ]
We'vejust landed here on what
cap troopers are calling Big "K"...

934
01:02:32,646 --> 01:02:35,114
with the Sixth Mobile
Infantry Division.

935
01:02:35,166 --> 01:02:37,999
It's an ugly planet,
a Bug planet...

936
01:02:38,046 --> 01:02:40,276
a planet hostile to life as we--

937
01:02:42,366 --> 01:02:45,403
Aaaah!

938
01:02:45,446 --> 01:02:47,960
Help me!
[ Screaming Continues ]

939
01:02:50,886 --> 01:02:52,763
Cut right!

940
01:03:03,486 --> 01:03:06,159
Come on!
Go, go, go!

941
01:03:06,206 --> 01:03:08,083
Get outta here now!

942
01:03:08,126 --> 01:03:10,003
- [ Bugs Screeching ]
- [ Shouting Continues ]

943
01:03:10,046 --> 01:03:12,879
-Watch your step!
-Watch your flanks! Watch your flanks!

944
01:03:15,646 --> 01:03:16,920
[ Bug Roars ]

945
01:03:16,966 --> 01:03:19,321
[ Screaming ]

946
01:03:23,006 --> 01:03:25,236
Kitten! No!

947
01:03:29,806 --> 01:03:31,797
[ Groans ]

948
01:03:41,566 --> 01:03:43,716
[ Screeching ]

949
01:03:48,926 --> 01:03:51,645
Aaaah!
[ Groans ]

950
01:03:51,726 --> 01:03:54,843
[ Screaming Continues ]

951
01:04:12,926 --> 01:04:15,918
Aaaaah!

952
01:04:28,166 --> 01:04:30,043
[ Narrator ]
Crisis for humankind.

953
01:04:30,086 --> 01:04:35,638
Fleet officials
admit they underestimated
the Arachnid's defensive capability.

954
01:04:35,726 --> 01:04:37,682
Accepting responsibility
for Klendathu...

955
01:04:37,726 --> 01:04:40,798
Sky Marshal Dienes resigns.

956
01:04:40,886 --> 01:04:45,880
His successor, Sky Marshal Tahat Meru,
outlines her new strategy.

957
01:04:45,926 --> 01:04:47,882
To fight the Bug...

958
01:04:47,966 --> 01:04:50,480
we must understand the Bug.

959
01:04:50,526 --> 01:04:53,359
We can ill afford
another Klendathu.

960
01:04:55,806 --> 01:04:57,637
[ Narrator ] Federal scientists
struggle to explain...

961
01:04:57,726 --> 01:05:00,604
the intelligent military actions
of the Arachnids.

962
01:05:00,646 --> 01:05:02,523
When a colony
reaches a certain size--

963
01:05:02,566 --> 01:05:05,319
300 generations or something--
it gets smarter.

964
01:05:05,406 --> 01:05:07,681
Insects with intelligence?
Have you ever met one?

965
01:05:07,766 --> 01:05:09,722
I can't believe
I am hearing this nonsense.

966
01:05:09,766 --> 01:05:13,315
-Just wait a moment--
- This is the most ridiculous
conversation I have ever had--

967
01:05:13,406 --> 01:05:17,001
Maybe there is some kind of bug
that we haven't seen yet--

968
01:05:17,086 --> 01:05:19,395
a leadership caste
of hive brains.

969
01:05:19,486 --> 01:05:24,196
Brain Bugs? Frankly, I find the idea
of a Bug that thinks offensive!

970
01:05:37,246 --> 01:05:40,124
Ticonderoga, this is Rodger Young
requesting approach vector.

971
01:05:40,166 --> 01:05:42,760
[ On Radio ]
Affirmative, Rodger Young.

972
01:05:42,846 --> 01:05:46,759
One-zero-zero-niner-five-two.
Welcome back.

973
01:05:48,246 --> 01:05:50,077
My God.

974
01:05:51,966 --> 01:05:54,002
How could this happen?

975
01:05:54,046 --> 01:05:56,879
We thought we were smarter
than the Bugs.

976
01:06:11,526 --> 01:06:14,836
- [ Shouting, Chattering ]
- Gimme somethin'! Please!

977
01:06:14,886 --> 01:06:17,241
It hurts!

978
01:06:17,286 --> 01:06:20,119
[ Nurse ] A-positive!
We're gonna need two litres!

979
01:06:21,606 --> 01:06:23,483
Be right with you.

980
01:06:23,526 --> 01:06:27,314
[ Groaning ]
Help me.

981
01:06:27,366 --> 01:06:29,243
God!

982
01:06:33,486 --> 01:06:36,284
It's strange.
There's almost no wounded at all.

983
01:06:36,366 --> 01:06:38,197
Bugs don't take prisoners.

984
01:06:47,166 --> 01:06:48,997
Oh, no.

985
01:06:49,086 --> 01:06:50,917
[ Trooper ]
Look!

986
01:06:55,246 --> 01:06:57,077
- Carmen--
- [ Sobs ]

987
01:07:18,326 --> 01:07:21,124
- Heh-heh. There he is.
- Let's wake him up.

988
01:07:21,206 --> 01:07:23,515
- Hey,Johnny! Hey!
- [ Chuckling ]

989
01:07:25,086 --> 01:07:27,122
Hey, Rico!

990
01:07:27,166 --> 01:07:29,885
- [ Dizzy Pounding Glass ]
Hey, Johnny! Wake up!
- How you doin', fish boy?

991
01:07:29,926 --> 01:07:32,759
Hey, look!
You're dead!

992
01:07:32,806 --> 01:07:35,036
Killed in action!

993
01:07:37,206 --> 01:07:39,800
- Three more days and you're out.
- Three days.

994
01:07:39,846 --> 01:07:42,076
- Good as new. See you later.
- Bye.

995
01:08:09,726 --> 01:08:12,081
So, what do you hear
about our new unit?

996
01:08:12,126 --> 01:08:14,959
Roughnecks killed more Bugs
than any other outfit on Big "K."

997
01:08:15,006 --> 01:08:18,316
Yeah, well, I hear their lieutenant
is a real nut-buster.

998
01:08:19,926 --> 01:08:21,757
Who's top kick?

999
01:08:21,846 --> 01:08:23,677
[ Weapon Cocks ]

1000
01:08:23,766 --> 01:08:25,836
You want the job, huh?

1001
01:08:25,886 --> 01:08:27,763
I wouldn't mind.

1002
01:08:27,806 --> 01:08:30,081
I would.

1003
01:08:30,166 --> 01:08:31,758
Just doin' my part.

1004
01:08:31,806 --> 01:08:34,957
Orders.

1005
01:08:35,006 --> 01:08:36,883
Yours?

1006
01:08:36,926 --> 01:08:38,803
Where you been besides Big "K"?

1007
01:08:38,846 --> 01:08:41,201
Outer Ring. Zegema Beach.

1008
01:08:41,246 --> 01:08:44,079
Zegema Beach.
I always wanted to go there.

1009
01:08:44,126 --> 01:08:46,196
Good luck.
It's not there any more.

1010
01:08:46,286 --> 01:08:50,040
So, I hear your lieutenant
is a real nut-buster.

1011
01:08:53,486 --> 01:08:56,159
No one talks about
the lieutenant that way.

1012
01:08:56,246 --> 01:08:58,077
- He saved my life.
- Mine too.

1013
01:08:59,366 --> 01:09:01,243
- Same for me.
- Me too.

1014
01:09:02,686 --> 01:09:05,405
Well, sounds like
he's quite a guy.

1015
01:09:05,486 --> 01:09:07,442
Who do you think
saved your ass?

1016
01:09:07,486 --> 01:09:09,363
[ Sergeant ]
Stand by.

1017
01:09:09,406 --> 01:09:11,840
Attention on deck.

1018
01:09:23,326 --> 01:09:25,635
This is for you new people.

1019
01:09:25,726 --> 01:09:27,682
I only have one rule.

1020
01:09:27,766 --> 01:09:31,042
Everyone fights.
No one quits.

1021
01:09:31,126 --> 01:09:33,924
You don't do your job,
I'll shoot you.

1022
01:09:34,006 --> 01:09:37,282
- Do you get me?
- We get you, sir!

1023
01:09:38,486 --> 01:09:40,317
Welcome to the Roughnecks.

1024
01:09:40,406 --> 01:09:42,283
- Rasczak's Roughnecks!
- [ All Grunt ]

1025
01:09:42,366 --> 01:09:44,197
At ease.
Listen up!

1026
01:09:44,286 --> 01:09:47,562
Got a new sky marshal
and a new battle plan.

1027
01:09:47,646 --> 01:09:52,356
Gonna clean out the systems outlying
Klendathu one planet at a time.

1028
01:09:52,446 --> 01:09:54,755
Tomorrow we hit
Tango Urilla.

1029
01:09:54,846 --> 01:09:58,361
After Fleet glasses the planet,
M.I. mops up.

1030
01:09:58,446 --> 01:10:00,277
Carry on.

1031
01:10:00,366 --> 01:10:02,675
[ Screeching, Roaring ]

1032
01:10:48,206 --> 01:10:50,515
All right, spread out!

1033
01:10:50,606 --> 01:10:54,519
Fire teams!
You locate a Bug hole, nuke it.

1034
01:11:01,726 --> 01:11:03,762
Watkins, take out Flores and Rico.

1035
01:11:03,806 --> 01:11:06,161
Copy that.
Move out!

1036
01:11:06,206 --> 01:11:09,039
[ Birdie ] First Platoon,
we're going for that ridge.

1037
01:11:09,086 --> 01:11:11,919
- Levy, you're with me.
- No, I'm with " A "squad.
I'm goin' with Rico.

1038
01:11:11,966 --> 01:11:14,036
Shut up and follow me!

1039
01:11:36,766 --> 01:11:38,643
[ Shrieking ]

1040
01:11:43,486 --> 01:11:45,317
[ Groans ]

1041
01:11:46,526 --> 01:11:48,437
[ Shrieking Weakly ]

1042
01:11:50,206 --> 01:11:51,958
Huh? You like that?

1043
01:11:52,046 --> 01:11:54,002
Monkey-sucking sack
of maggot puke!

1044
01:11:54,046 --> 01:11:55,638
It's dead, Watkins! It's dead!

1045
01:11:59,966 --> 01:12:02,764
Ain't much to look at
after you scrape 'em off your boot.

1046
01:12:04,006 --> 01:12:06,839
Bug hole. There.

1047
01:12:08,686 --> 01:12:10,802
[ Weapon Firing ]

1048
01:12:14,766 --> 01:12:17,883
[ Screeching, Roaring ]

1049
01:12:20,926 --> 01:12:23,121
Nuke 'em, Rico!

1050
01:12:27,806 --> 01:12:29,319
- [ Beeping ]
- Fire in the hole!

1051
01:12:39,526 --> 01:12:42,757
[ Birdie On Radio ]
We're under heavy attack, position M-4.

1052
01:12:42,846 --> 01:12:45,076
- Get over here!
- Move!

1053
01:12:54,686 --> 01:12:57,678
- You got a Bug problem, ma'am?
- Aw, stow it, Trooper!

1054
01:13:17,486 --> 01:13:19,317
Tanker!

1055
01:13:20,326 --> 01:13:23,398
- Oh, shit!
- Come on. Move!

1056
01:13:31,646 --> 01:13:33,557
Get down!

1057
01:13:38,126 --> 01:13:40,515
[ Screaming ]

1058
01:13:40,606 --> 01:13:42,517
Come on!

1059
01:14:17,006 --> 01:14:19,236
[ Grunting ]

1060
01:14:27,646 --> 01:14:29,796
- [ Beeping ]
- Aaaah!

1061
01:14:42,886 --> 01:14:45,195
[ Troopers Shouting,
Hooting, Cheering ]

1062
01:14:47,646 --> 01:14:50,001
[ Trooper Shouting, Laughing ]

1063
01:14:50,046 --> 01:14:51,843
- Come on.
- [ Grunting ]

1064
01:14:51,926 --> 01:14:53,996
[ Rasczak Grunts ]
Call for retrieval.

1065
01:14:54,046 --> 01:14:55,923
- Medic!
- Nice moves.

1066
01:14:55,966 --> 01:14:58,799
Where'd you learn
how to do that, soldier?

1067
01:14:58,846 --> 01:15:01,679
Back in school, sir.
Don't you remember?

1068
01:15:01,726 --> 01:15:03,603
I was captain of the team.

1069
01:15:04,806 --> 01:15:06,524
- Rico.
- Sir.

1070
01:15:06,606 --> 01:15:08,437
I need a corporal.

1071
01:15:08,526 --> 01:15:12,075
You're it until you're dead,
or until I find somebody better.

1072
01:15:12,126 --> 01:15:14,481
Thank you, sir.

1073
01:15:14,526 --> 01:15:17,404
- All right, saddle up!
- Way to go, Corporal!

1074
01:15:17,486 --> 01:15:19,716
Hey, I need a squad leader.

1075
01:15:19,806 --> 01:15:22,115
Oh, no. No.
I've been there. I blew it.

1076
01:15:22,206 --> 01:15:24,117
I'm just here to fight.

1077
01:15:24,166 --> 01:15:26,202
What about it, Diz?

1078
01:15:29,486 --> 01:15:31,317
Looks like I'm your girl, sir.

1079
01:15:31,406 --> 01:15:34,842
- [ Laughing ]
- [ Together ] Ooh-aaah!

1080
01:15:35,526 --> 01:15:37,801
- [ Chattering ]
- [ Laughing ] Catch ya later.

1081
01:15:40,366 --> 01:15:42,197
Go.

1082
01:15:43,246 --> 01:15:45,077
Listen up!

1083
01:15:45,166 --> 01:15:48,363
I expect the best,
and I give the best!

1084
01:15:51,646 --> 01:15:53,955
- Here's the beer!
- [ Cheering, Whistling ]

1085
01:15:57,006 --> 01:15:59,804
- Here's the entertainment!
- [ Shouting, Cheering Continues ]

1086
01:16:03,006 --> 01:16:05,520
Have fun!
That's an order!

1087
01:16:05,566 --> 01:16:07,602
[ Trooper ]
This one's for me!

1088
01:16:07,646 --> 01:16:10,956
- Whoo!
- Thank you, Lieutenant!

1089
01:16:12,446 --> 01:16:15,119
-** [ Violin.: "Dixie" ]
- Rico.

1090
01:16:16,446 --> 01:16:18,323
You kill Bugs good.

1091
01:16:18,366 --> 01:16:20,243
Thanks.

1092
01:16:20,286 --> 01:16:22,163
[ Cheering, Shouting Continue ]

1093
01:16:22,206 --> 01:16:25,994
You knew the lieutenant
before the war. What was he like?

1094
01:16:26,046 --> 01:16:29,356
-** [ Continues ]
- He was a teacher.
Kind of like he knew it all.

1095
01:16:29,406 --> 01:16:31,761
He always had this little smile.

1096
01:16:31,806 --> 01:16:34,161
Yeah, well,
he don't smile much any more.

1097
01:16:34,206 --> 01:16:37,994
Well, I guess your bottle fills up
real quick when your kids get smeared--

1098
01:16:38,046 --> 01:16:40,765
- Come on, Corporal.
- Oh, no. I don't do that any more.

1099
01:16:40,846 --> 01:16:44,759
- I remember when you
used to dance. Come on.
- Do I have to pull rank?

1100
01:16:47,206 --> 01:16:49,083
Excuse me, sir.

1101
01:16:50,446 --> 01:16:53,244
** [ Continues ]

1102
01:16:57,166 --> 01:16:59,316
Rico.

1103
01:16:59,366 --> 01:17:02,199
You once asked me for advice.
You want some now?

1104
01:17:02,246 --> 01:17:05,079
- Yes, sir.
- Lieutenant, H.Q.'s on the com.

1105
01:17:07,046 --> 01:17:09,321
Never pass up a good thing.

1106
01:17:12,286 --> 01:17:15,084
** [ Continues ]

1107
01:17:17,246 --> 01:17:20,079
- Watkins. Beer?
-** [ Ends ]

1108
01:17:20,126 --> 01:17:22,959
[ Applause, Cheering ]

1109
01:17:24,606 --> 01:17:27,916
** [ Slow Ballad ]

1110
01:17:31,326 --> 01:17:33,203
[ Giggles ]

1111
01:17:41,406 --> 01:17:44,443
So, Rico, what are you doin'
after the dance?

1112
01:17:50,846 --> 01:17:52,723
[ Grunts ]

1113
01:17:58,006 --> 01:17:59,837
[ Whispers ]
Come on.

1114
01:18:23,726 --> 01:18:26,240
[ Chuckles ]

1115
01:18:29,526 --> 01:18:31,357
What's so funny?

1116
01:18:32,766 --> 01:18:35,564
You know, just the way
things work out.

1117
01:18:51,686 --> 01:18:54,041
We finally got together, Diz.

1118
01:18:56,966 --> 01:18:59,799
I love you,Johnny.

1119
01:19:08,966 --> 01:19:10,479
[ Rasczak ]
Rico!

1120
01:19:12,606 --> 01:19:15,439
We're moving out.
There's been a distress call
from General Owen on planet "P."

1121
01:19:15,486 --> 01:19:18,956
- So get your shit wired
and report in ten minutes.
- Yes, sir.

1122
01:19:19,006 --> 01:19:20,564
Who's that with you?

1123
01:19:23,886 --> 01:19:26,002
Flores, sir.

1124
01:19:26,046 --> 01:19:28,401
Make it 20 minutes.

1125
01:19:28,446 --> 01:19:30,323
[ Rico ]
Yes, sir.

1126
01:19:30,366 --> 01:19:32,277
[ Giggles ]
Twenty minutes?

1127
01:19:33,766 --> 01:19:35,643
We can do it.

1128
01:20:11,326 --> 01:20:13,157
Whisky to Outpost.
Do you copy?

1129
01:20:13,246 --> 01:20:17,637
This is Roughneck Two-Zero
on tack three. Come in, please.

1130
01:20:17,726 --> 01:20:21,480
Whisky, Outpost. This is
Roughneck Two-Zero on tack three.

1131
01:20:21,566 --> 01:20:23,397
- Make contact with General Owen?
- No, sir.

1132
01:20:23,486 --> 01:20:25,317
Not even the transponder signal.

1133
01:20:25,406 --> 01:20:28,443
It's these canyons.
Go to higher ground, Sergeant.

1134
01:20:34,086 --> 01:20:35,917
Whisky, Outpost.
Whisky, Outpost.

1135
01:20:35,966 --> 01:20:38,196
- This is Roughneck Two-Zero on--
- [ Screeching ]

1136
01:20:40,926 --> 01:20:42,996
[ Sergeant Screaming ]

1137
01:20:44,446 --> 01:20:46,357
[ Screaming Continues ]

1138
01:20:49,326 --> 01:20:51,157
Sugar, your weapon.

1139
01:20:56,646 --> 01:20:59,479
Help me! H-- Aaah!

1140
01:20:59,526 --> 01:21:01,403
[ Screaming Continues ]

1141
01:21:09,326 --> 01:21:12,921
I'd expect anyone in this unit
to do the same for me.

1142
01:21:13,926 --> 01:21:15,803
- Rico.
- Sir.

1143
01:21:15,846 --> 01:21:17,723
You're acting sergeant.
Move 'em out.

1144
01:21:19,006 --> 01:21:21,520
You heard the lieutenant!
Saddle up!

1145
01:22:07,846 --> 01:22:09,564
[ Groans ]

1146
01:22:11,326 --> 01:22:14,636
Gee, someone really
humped the bunk.

1147
01:22:14,686 --> 01:22:17,041
- Watkins.
- Sir.

1148
01:22:17,086 --> 01:22:19,919
- Secure this compound.
Police these bodies.
- Yes, sir.

1149
01:22:19,966 --> 01:22:22,526
- Give me three up on the tower, now!
-Aye-aye!

1150
01:22:22,606 --> 01:22:24,437
O.P. there!
O.P. there!

1151
01:22:24,526 --> 01:22:27,086
Siren Two, police up these bodies!

1152
01:22:27,166 --> 01:22:28,997
Whew. Stinks in there.

1153
01:22:29,086 --> 01:22:30,838
- Rico!
- Yes, sir.

1154
01:22:30,926 --> 01:22:32,757
We need retrieval.
This place crawls.

1155
01:22:32,846 --> 01:22:35,644
Get somebody in a communications tent
and get me an uplink.

1156
01:22:35,726 --> 01:22:37,557
Yes, sir.
Diz, check it out.

1157
01:22:37,646 --> 01:22:39,477
[ Rasczak ]
Command group with me.

1158
01:22:42,286 --> 01:22:44,117
Ah, shit.

1159
01:22:44,206 --> 01:22:46,037
Lieutenant.

1160
01:22:48,366 --> 01:22:51,324
Dirty Bugs came in
right while they were having chow.

1161
01:22:51,366 --> 01:22:53,243
Ugh.

1162
01:22:55,486 --> 01:22:57,238
Yeah.

1163
01:22:57,326 --> 01:22:59,157
This is where they got in.

1164
01:23:00,606 --> 01:23:02,483
Lieutenant.

1165
01:23:02,526 --> 01:23:05,359
I think you're gonna
want to see this.

1166
01:23:05,406 --> 01:23:07,283
What do you got, Flores?

1167
01:23:07,326 --> 01:23:09,203
[ Ace ]
God, I hate this place.

1168
01:23:23,446 --> 01:23:25,801
What's that look like
to you, Rico?

1169
01:23:28,606 --> 01:23:31,643
Looks like a Bug
was in his brain, sir.

1170
01:23:31,686 --> 01:23:33,563
[ Squish ]

1171
01:23:36,006 --> 01:23:38,201
[ Gasps, Swallows ]

1172
01:23:39,646 --> 01:23:42,035
They sucked his brains out.

1173
01:23:43,166 --> 01:23:44,997
[ Crash ]

1174
01:23:48,446 --> 01:23:50,801
[ Rattling, Crashing ]

1175
01:23:50,846 --> 01:23:52,723
Open that.

1176
01:23:52,766 --> 01:23:55,485
Aaaah! Aaah!

1177
01:23:55,566 --> 01:23:57,397
Officer on the deck!

1178
01:23:57,486 --> 01:23:59,920
- Pick up the general.
- [ General ] Cohen?

1179
01:23:59,966 --> 01:24:02,526
- Is it safe?
We gotta get out of here!
- General.

1180
01:24:02,606 --> 01:24:04,756
Sir!

1181
01:24:04,846 --> 01:24:06,677
[ Exhales ]

1182
01:24:06,766 --> 01:24:08,597
Thank God for you.

1183
01:24:08,686 --> 01:24:10,517
- All of you.
- [ Muttering ] Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

1184
01:24:10,606 --> 01:24:13,404
You're all gonna be heroes,
every last one of you.

1185
01:24:13,486 --> 01:24:14,965
Close that hole.

1186
01:24:15,006 --> 01:24:16,405
Yes, sir.

1187
01:24:16,446 --> 01:24:18,323
I had to evade capture.

1188
01:24:18,366 --> 01:24:21,244
- The security of the Federation
was at stake.
- Fire in the hole!

1189
01:24:21,286 --> 01:24:23,163
[ Explosion ]

1190
01:24:23,206 --> 01:24:26,357
I have operational knowledge
of what we're up to out here.

1191
01:24:26,406 --> 01:24:28,362
- Flores, I need that uplink.
- Working on it, sir.

1192
01:24:28,446 --> 01:24:30,277
- Damn it.
- [ General ] See?

1193
01:24:30,366 --> 01:24:33,483
They get in your mind.
Look. They did it to Farley.

1194
01:24:33,566 --> 01:24:37,036
They got into his mind.
They make you do things.

1195
01:24:37,086 --> 01:24:38,678
They made Farley
call headquarters.

1196
01:24:38,766 --> 01:24:40,597
The distress call was a trap.

1197
01:24:40,686 --> 01:24:43,803
They're just like us.
They want to know what makes us tick.

1198
01:24:43,846 --> 01:24:46,485
They wanna know us
so they can kill us.

1199
01:24:46,526 --> 01:24:48,403
Roughnecks, this is Lead.
Prepare for attack.

1200
01:24:48,446 --> 01:24:50,357
Where's the retrieval boat?

1201
01:24:50,446 --> 01:24:52,880
Mayday. This is Roughneck Two-Zero
to battle group. Do you read?

1202
01:24:52,926 --> 01:24:56,123
Oh, God!
We're gonna die!

1203
01:24:56,166 --> 01:24:58,999
Don't you understand?
We're all gonna die!

1204
01:24:59,046 --> 01:25:01,799
[ Groaning ]

1205
01:25:01,886 --> 01:25:03,717
Control yourself, General.

1206
01:25:03,806 --> 01:25:06,115
I can't. I can't.

1207
01:25:06,206 --> 01:25:08,037
I wish you'd just shoot me.

1208
01:25:08,126 --> 01:25:10,515
- [ Weapons Cocks ]
- [ Whimpers ]

1209
01:25:10,606 --> 01:25:13,564
Lieutenant! He's just
a little out of his mind, sir.

1210
01:25:14,686 --> 01:25:16,563
Bugs! Bugs!

1211
01:25:16,606 --> 01:25:18,597
- Die! [ Whimpers ]
- All right.

1212
01:25:18,686 --> 01:25:22,440
Warm it all up!
Everything you've got!

1213
01:25:22,526 --> 01:25:25,404
Come on, you apes!
You wanna live forever?

1214
01:25:27,526 --> 01:25:28,925
[ Trooper ]
I got Bugs!

1215
01:25:29,006 --> 01:25:31,315
[ Shouting ]

1216
01:25:40,606 --> 01:25:43,404
[ Screeching ]

1217
01:25:45,286 --> 01:25:48,119
- [ Trooper ] Magazine!
- [ Weapons Cocking ]

1218
01:25:57,486 --> 01:25:59,317
Fire at will!

1219
01:26:04,446 --> 01:26:06,596
Yaaaah!

1220
01:26:27,686 --> 01:26:29,995
Yaaaah!

1221
01:26:38,046 --> 01:26:40,435
Incoming!

1222
01:26:52,606 --> 01:26:54,039
Ohh! Ohh!

1223
01:26:56,206 --> 01:26:57,798
Aaaah!

1224
01:27:01,246 --> 01:27:03,635
No! Aaah!

1225
01:27:07,206 --> 01:27:10,039
[ Troopers Shouting ]

1226
01:27:10,126 --> 01:27:11,957
Rico!
Where's my communications?

1227
01:27:12,046 --> 01:27:14,355
- Diz, status on the uplink?
- Give me a minute!

1228
01:27:14,446 --> 01:27:16,277
We don't have a minute!

1229
01:27:25,126 --> 01:27:28,084
- Battle Group,
this is Roughneck Two-Zero.
- This is Rodger Young. Go ahead.

1230
01:27:28,126 --> 01:27:30,959
We are under attack, sir.
We need retrieval now!

1231
01:27:31,006 --> 01:27:33,839
- We have planet "P"as clear.
- This place crawls, sir.
We need pickup now!

1232
01:27:33,886 --> 01:27:36,241
- What's your position?
- Come down on this transmission.

1233
01:27:36,286 --> 01:27:39,596
- The outpost? That's crazy!
- I hope you have a crazy pilot! Out!

1234
01:27:53,086 --> 01:27:54,599
[ Yelling ]

1235
01:28:10,046 --> 01:28:11,877
Lieutenant!

1236
01:28:11,966 --> 01:28:13,797
Boat coming down, sir!

1237
01:28:13,886 --> 01:28:15,717
Fall back into the compound!

1238
01:28:15,806 --> 01:28:17,558
Fall back!

1239
01:28:41,206 --> 01:28:43,037
Hold here!
Hold what you got!

1240
01:28:43,126 --> 01:28:44,718
Aaaah!

1241
01:28:53,726 --> 01:28:55,159
Running low!

1242
01:28:55,246 --> 01:28:57,555
- [ Chamber Clicking ]
- I'm out!

1243
01:28:57,646 --> 01:29:00,001
Here! Make 'em count!

1244
01:29:18,526 --> 01:29:20,437
Make cover fire!
Fall back!

1245
01:29:35,806 --> 01:29:37,637
Move! Move! Move!

1246
01:29:39,646 --> 01:29:42,444
Fall back to the boat!
Haul ass!

1247
01:29:42,526 --> 01:29:44,118
[ Rumbling ]

1248
01:29:45,886 --> 01:29:47,638
Yaaaah!

1249
01:29:48,646 --> 01:29:50,477
[ Grunting ]

1250
01:29:53,206 --> 01:29:55,322
Aaah! Aaah!

1251
01:29:55,366 --> 01:29:57,402
- Oh, my God!
- Ohh!

1252
01:29:57,446 --> 01:30:00,483
[ Screaming ]

1253
01:30:00,566 --> 01:30:03,444
- Get him clear!
- Aaah!

1254
01:30:09,246 --> 01:30:11,396
Rico-- Aaaah! Rico!

1255
01:30:12,606 --> 01:30:15,439
- You know what to do!
- Yes, sir!

1256
01:30:16,446 --> 01:30:19,006
[ Weapon Cocks ]

1257
01:30:20,286 --> 01:30:21,924
Do it, Rico!

1258
01:30:43,446 --> 01:30:46,756
Whoo-hoo! Yeah!

1259
01:30:46,846 --> 01:30:48,643
Dizzy!

1260
01:30:56,126 --> 01:30:58,435
No! No!
[ Screaming ]

1261
01:31:08,886 --> 01:31:11,195
- No!
- [ Coughing, Groaning ]

1262
01:31:11,286 --> 01:31:14,835
Ace, help me!
Hold her down!

1263
01:31:14,886 --> 01:31:17,844
[ Screaming ]

1264
01:31:18,846 --> 01:31:20,882
Move! Get her into the boat!

1265
01:31:20,926 --> 01:31:23,520
- [ Coughing ]
- Come on, Diz. Don't die on me.

1266
01:31:23,606 --> 01:31:25,437
Get her out!
Let's go! Let's go!

1267
01:31:25,526 --> 01:31:27,198
[ Trooper ]
Go, go, go!

1268
01:31:30,566 --> 01:31:33,160
Let's go!
Get aboard!

1269
01:31:34,526 --> 01:31:36,403
Tower, let's go!

1270
01:31:43,166 --> 01:31:46,203
Let's move it, Tower! Run!

1271
01:31:51,806 --> 01:31:53,364
Lift off!

1272
01:32:21,246 --> 01:32:23,077
[ Gagging ]

1273
01:32:23,166 --> 01:32:25,122
Johnny, I'm dying-- dying.

1274
01:32:25,206 --> 01:32:28,004
No. You're gonna be
all right, Diz.

1275
01:32:28,086 --> 01:32:30,884
[ Gasping ]
It's all right...

1276
01:32:32,286 --> 01:32:34,720
because I got to have you.

1277
01:32:34,806 --> 01:32:36,797
[ Quiet Sob ]

1278
01:32:38,206 --> 01:32:40,481
[ Panting, Gagging ]

1279
01:32:40,566 --> 01:32:43,763
[ Coughing ]
Johnny, don't let me go!

1280
01:32:43,806 --> 01:32:45,478
J--J--

1281
01:32:45,566 --> 01:32:47,602
[ Coughing ]
Don't let-- Don't let--

1282
01:33:04,726 --> 01:33:06,557
[ On Radio ]
This is Battle Control.

1283
01:33:06,646 --> 01:33:09,285
Proceed on vector
five-niner-two-two-seven.

1284
01:33:10,326 --> 01:33:12,396
I think you should know...

1285
01:33:13,886 --> 01:33:16,195
your friend Rico is back there.

1286
01:33:24,886 --> 01:33:28,322
Get on the com and tell Fleet
to blast that rock.

1287
01:33:28,406 --> 01:33:30,283
On whose authority, Corporal?

1288
01:33:30,366 --> 01:33:33,438
That would be mine, sir.
I assumed command of the mission.

1289
01:33:34,646 --> 01:33:37,444
Rodger Young,
we have an official request...

1290
01:33:37,526 --> 01:33:39,357
by the Mobile Infantry...

1291
01:33:39,446 --> 01:33:41,323
to commence bombardment
of planet "P."

1292
01:33:41,406 --> 01:33:43,761
I thought you were dead.

1293
01:33:43,806 --> 01:33:46,764
I'm not, but a lot
of my troopers are.

1294
01:33:46,846 --> 01:33:50,282
Negative on your request. The sky
marshal has other plans for planet "P. "

1295
01:33:50,366 --> 01:33:52,197
Welcome back.

1296
01:33:52,286 --> 01:33:55,244
M.I. does the dying,
and Fleet just does the flying.

1297
01:33:55,326 --> 01:33:57,965
Hold on.
Something's up.

1298
01:33:58,046 --> 01:34:01,322
Fleet's mobilized
for a big operation.

1299
01:34:27,446 --> 01:34:29,357
Attention on deck!

1300
01:34:35,886 --> 01:34:37,922
Once, somebody asked me...

1301
01:34:38,006 --> 01:34:41,999
if I knew the difference
between a citizen and a civilian.

1302
01:34:42,046 --> 01:34:44,765
I can tell you now.

1303
01:34:44,806 --> 01:34:47,639
A citizen has the courage
to make the safety of the human race...

1304
01:34:47,686 --> 01:34:50,405
their personal responsibility.

1305
01:34:54,086 --> 01:34:56,600
Dizzy was my friend.

1306
01:34:56,646 --> 01:34:58,682
She was a soldier...

1307
01:34:58,726 --> 01:35:00,682
but more than that...

1308
01:35:00,766 --> 01:35:03,121
she was a citizen
of the Federation.

1309
01:35:05,286 --> 01:35:07,277
Present arms!

1310
01:35:24,766 --> 01:35:27,724
Order arms!

1311
01:35:30,846 --> 01:35:33,565
Left face!

1312
01:35:46,166 --> 01:35:48,122
- Officer on deck.
- Carry on.

1313
01:35:49,446 --> 01:35:52,085
Burial detail, dismissed.

1314
01:35:58,326 --> 01:36:00,203
At ease.

1315
01:36:00,286 --> 01:36:02,117
How are you, Carl?

1316
01:36:02,206 --> 01:36:04,037
Carmen, good.

1317
01:36:04,126 --> 01:36:06,924
Johnny, I'm sorry
it had to be your unit on "P."

1318
01:36:07,006 --> 01:36:09,566
That mission had
a very low survival probability.

1319
01:36:09,606 --> 01:36:12,643
The Bugs laid a trap for us,
didn't they?

1320
01:36:12,726 --> 01:36:14,842
Elegant proof of intelligence,
isn't it?

1321
01:36:14,886 --> 01:36:17,719
I thought there might be
a Brain Bug on "P."

1322
01:36:17,766 --> 01:36:19,643
You knew, and you sent them anyway?

1323
01:36:19,686 --> 01:36:23,042
We couldn't afford to launch
an operation if there wasn't one.

1324
01:36:24,126 --> 01:36:26,003
You don't approve.

1325
01:36:26,046 --> 01:36:27,923
Well, too bad.

1326
01:36:27,966 --> 01:36:31,038
We're in this for the species,
boys and girls. It's simple numbers.

1327
01:36:31,126 --> 01:36:33,242
They have more...

1328
01:36:33,286 --> 01:36:37,245
and every day I have to make decisions
that send hundreds of people
like you to their deaths.

1329
01:36:37,286 --> 01:36:39,242
Didn't they tell you, Colonel?

1330
01:36:39,326 --> 01:36:41,601
That's what
the Mobile Infantry's good for.

1331
01:36:41,686 --> 01:36:44,154
I hope you're ready for more.

1332
01:36:44,246 --> 01:36:47,636
We're going back to "P"
to capture that Brain.

1333
01:36:49,366 --> 01:36:51,960
The Roughnecks
are always ready, sir.

1334
01:36:52,046 --> 01:36:54,799
I hear they need a new lieutenant.
Want the job?

1335
01:36:54,846 --> 01:36:58,805
I'll take it, until I get killed
or you find someone better.

1336
01:37:02,086 --> 01:37:04,998
[ Sighs ]
Well?

1337
01:37:07,166 --> 01:37:08,997
Take care of yourself,Johnny.

1338
01:37:09,086 --> 01:37:10,917
I'll see you again.

1339
01:37:23,846 --> 01:37:25,723
Officer on deck!

1340
01:37:41,246 --> 01:37:43,077
Who are all these kids?

1341
01:37:43,166 --> 01:37:45,122
We got reinforced.

1342
01:37:45,206 --> 01:37:47,401
Most of them
are fresh out of boot.

1343
01:37:47,486 --> 01:37:49,317
We're the old men, Ace.

1344
01:37:51,406 --> 01:37:53,681
This is for all you new people.

1345
01:37:53,726 --> 01:37:55,842
I only have one rule:

1346
01:37:55,926 --> 01:37:58,998
Everyone fights.
No one quits.

1347
01:37:59,046 --> 01:38:02,038
You don't do your job,
I'll kill you myself.

1348
01:38:02,126 --> 01:38:05,436
- Do you get me?
- We get you, sir!

1349
01:38:05,526 --> 01:38:07,437
Welcome to the Roughnecks.

1350
01:38:07,486 --> 01:38:10,080
- Rico's Roughnecks!
- [ Soldiers Shout ]

1351
01:38:12,446 --> 01:38:15,244
Today we're gonna pay
a visit to Bug City.

1352
01:38:15,326 --> 01:38:18,238
We're lookin' for a Bug
no one's ever seen before.

1353
01:38:18,326 --> 01:38:20,157
Some kind of smart Bug.

1354
01:38:20,246 --> 01:38:22,077
[ Whooshing ]

1355
01:38:25,726 --> 01:38:27,557
And it probably knows we're coming.

1356
01:38:27,646 --> 01:38:29,477
Saddle up!

1357
01:38:29,566 --> 01:38:31,522
- Saddle up! Hyah!
- [ Shouting ]

1358
01:38:31,606 --> 01:38:33,437
Go, go, go, go, go!

1359
01:38:44,326 --> 01:38:46,362
Evasive action.

1360
01:39:08,606 --> 01:39:10,961
Get us clear for warp, Number Two.

1361
01:39:11,006 --> 01:39:12,883
Clear in five, four...

1362
01:39:12,926 --> 01:39:14,803
- Initiating star drive in five--
- three--

1363
01:39:16,126 --> 01:39:18,321
[ Yelling ]

1364
01:39:27,646 --> 01:39:29,318
[ Screaming ]

1365
01:39:37,086 --> 01:39:39,361
This is Rodger Young.
We're going down.

1366
01:39:39,446 --> 01:39:41,721
- Repeat. This is Rodger Young.
We're going down.
- Get out!

1367
01:39:41,766 --> 01:39:43,643
Abandon ship! Come on!

1368
01:39:46,126 --> 01:39:48,435
- Aaaaah!
- Zander!

1369
01:39:48,526 --> 01:39:51,324
- Here!
- We've got to get to
the rescue deck!

1370
01:39:51,406 --> 01:39:52,839
Come on!

1371
01:39:58,246 --> 01:40:00,601
[ Grunting ]

1372
01:40:06,086 --> 01:40:08,441
Aaaah!

1373
01:40:08,486 --> 01:40:10,363
- Captain!
-Aaaah!

1374
01:40:10,406 --> 01:40:12,681
[ Groaning ]

1375
01:40:12,766 --> 01:40:15,075
Abandon ship.
That's an--

1376
01:40:15,166 --> 01:40:16,997
[ Sighs ]

1377
01:40:17,086 --> 01:40:20,476
She's dead, Carmen!
She's dead!

1378
01:40:25,366 --> 01:40:27,800
[ Screaming, Shouting ]

1379
01:40:37,766 --> 01:40:40,121
- Here!
- [ Shouting Continues ]

1380
01:40:53,566 --> 01:40:55,796
Follow me!

1381
01:41:05,446 --> 01:41:07,323
Ready?

1382
01:41:13,446 --> 01:41:15,437
- Hit it!
- [ Engine Starting, Accelerating ]

1383
01:41:30,886 --> 01:41:34,037
Life pod Bravo 6-3, two aboard.

1384
01:41:41,686 --> 01:41:43,881
Scanning for a landing zone.

1385
01:41:43,966 --> 01:41:45,365
Checking terrain. Here!

1386
01:41:45,406 --> 01:41:48,318
- Can you handle that?
- Piece of cake.

1387
01:41:51,846 --> 01:41:54,121
[ On Radio ]
We've lost the Rodger Young.

1388
01:41:54,206 --> 01:41:57,721
Flight Command, we have confirmation.
The Rodger Young is down.

1389
01:41:57,766 --> 01:41:59,757
Aww!Johnny!

1390
01:41:59,806 --> 01:42:01,683
[ Grunts ]

1391
01:42:01,726 --> 01:42:03,603
Johnny!

1392
01:42:05,286 --> 01:42:07,163
Rodger Young just burned up.

1393
01:42:07,206 --> 01:42:09,083
It's on the rescue net.

1394
01:42:09,126 --> 01:42:11,481
[ Radio Chatter, Static ]

1395
01:42:11,526 --> 01:42:13,721
Any survivors?

1396
01:42:13,806 --> 01:42:15,956
Well, they're gettin'
tarred up there pretty bad.

1397
01:42:16,006 --> 01:42:18,918
Life pod Bravo 6-3, two aboard.
Is anyone receiving?

1398
01:42:19,006 --> 01:42:20,837
- [ Carmen ] Is anyone receiving?
- Affirmative!

1399
01:42:20,926 --> 01:42:23,394
- This is Roughneck Two-Zero.
- You're breaking up. Say again.

1400
01:42:23,486 --> 01:42:25,317
- Carmen?
- Say again! I'm losing you!

1401
01:42:25,406 --> 01:42:27,237
Carmen!

1402
01:42:30,886 --> 01:42:35,516
Prepare for landing!
Retro in three, two, one.

1403
01:42:35,606 --> 01:42:37,483
Fire!

1404
01:42:51,486 --> 01:42:53,636
Carmen. Carmen.

1405
01:42:53,726 --> 01:42:55,842
- Hey. You okay?
- Uh-huh.

1406
01:42:55,926 --> 01:42:57,359
Get out. Get out.

1407
01:43:00,286 --> 01:43:02,117
[ Hushed Screech ]

1408
01:43:06,366 --> 01:43:09,085
[ Radio Static ]
Are you receiving? Over.

1409
01:43:09,166 --> 01:43:11,964
This is Roughneck Two-Zero.
Carmen! Are you receiving?

1410
01:43:12,006 --> 01:43:13,883
Johnny, is that you?

1411
01:43:13,926 --> 01:43:16,486
Yeah, it's me!
What's your position and situation?

1412
01:43:16,566 --> 01:43:19,364
We're in Bug City,
20 metres underground, position:

1413
01:43:19,446 --> 01:43:21,277
south 42, east 118.

1414
01:43:21,366 --> 01:43:23,436
- Situation is--
- [ Hissing ]

1415
01:43:23,486 --> 01:43:25,363
[ Rico ]
I repeat, south 4 2, east 118.

1416
01:43:25,406 --> 01:43:27,601
[ Roaring ]

1417
01:43:27,646 --> 01:43:29,523
[ Rico ]
Carmen!

1418
01:43:31,166 --> 01:43:33,043
Situation is extremely hostile.

1419
01:43:37,726 --> 01:43:39,956
I need a squad to pull 'em out!
Direction!

1420
01:43:40,006 --> 01:43:41,883
Three clicks, south by southwest.

1421
01:43:48,006 --> 01:43:50,645
Look out!

1422
01:43:50,686 --> 01:43:53,075
[ Roaring, Snarling ]

1423
01:43:55,366 --> 01:43:57,561
[ Screaming ]

1424
01:44:00,726 --> 01:44:03,035
Aaaaah!

1425
01:44:03,126 --> 01:44:04,957
[ Radio.:Static ]

1426
01:44:07,286 --> 01:44:09,117
What do you wanna do?

1427
01:44:09,206 --> 01:44:11,845
You heard the lieutenant!
Rescue party!

1428
01:44:11,926 --> 01:44:14,042
Third squad, come with me!

1429
01:44:14,086 --> 01:44:16,554
Cancel that!

1430
01:44:16,606 --> 01:44:19,678
You know as well as I do
she's already dead.

1431
01:44:22,846 --> 01:44:24,677
Sorry, buddy.

1432
01:44:25,966 --> 01:44:29,242
Roughnecks, let's move.

1433
01:44:29,326 --> 01:44:31,635
All right.

1434
01:44:31,686 --> 01:44:34,041
[ Screeching ]

1435
01:44:42,686 --> 01:44:45,519
Aaaaaah!
[ Groans ]

1436
01:44:45,566 --> 01:44:47,557
Why didn't they kill us?

1437
01:44:47,646 --> 01:44:49,477
They want us alive.

1438
01:45:41,526 --> 01:45:43,835
We should go this way.

1439
01:45:44,966 --> 01:45:47,321
"A" company's that way.

1440
01:45:47,366 --> 01:45:49,243
Yeah...

1441
01:45:49,286 --> 01:45:51,277
but Carmen's down there.

1442
01:45:51,326 --> 01:45:53,681
Hey, I hate to be rude, buddy...

1443
01:45:53,726 --> 01:45:55,796
but word has it she's dead.

1444
01:45:55,846 --> 01:45:59,156
- She's still alive.
- How do you know?

1445
01:45:59,206 --> 01:46:01,401
I don't know how I know, but I know.

1446
01:46:01,446 --> 01:46:04,756
Listen, you got command,
but goin'off mission...

1447
01:46:04,806 --> 01:46:07,115
that's a serious offence.

1448
01:46:07,166 --> 01:46:09,157
Yeah. I think
they hang you for that.

1449
01:46:11,206 --> 01:46:14,881
Roughneck Two-Zero,
proceed on mission.

1450
01:46:14,966 --> 01:46:16,797
I need two volunteers.

1451
01:46:19,046 --> 01:46:20,923
[ Sighs ]

1452
01:46:22,766 --> 01:46:25,075
[ Screeching ]

1453
01:46:42,686 --> 01:46:44,916
Aaah!
[ Groaning ]

1454
01:46:59,926 --> 01:47:01,757
[ Roaring, Gurgling ]

1455
01:47:24,286 --> 01:47:26,356
One day...

1456
01:47:26,406 --> 01:47:28,601
someone like me...

1457
01:47:28,686 --> 01:47:30,358
is gonna kill you...

1458
01:47:30,446 --> 01:47:33,085
and your whole fucking race.

1459
01:47:38,606 --> 01:47:41,245
Aaaah!

1460
01:47:41,326 --> 01:47:43,635
[ Groaning ]

1461
01:47:49,366 --> 01:47:51,880
[ Panting ]

1462
01:47:51,966 --> 01:47:54,685
[ Gasping ]

1463
01:47:54,726 --> 01:47:56,842
[ Slurping ]

1464
01:47:59,846 --> 01:48:02,041
Aaaaah!

1465
01:48:07,966 --> 01:48:09,957
[ Roaring ]

1466
01:48:28,966 --> 01:48:30,843
You know what this is?

1467
01:48:30,886 --> 01:48:32,922
[ Makes Exploding Sound ]

1468
01:48:32,966 --> 01:48:35,161
- [ Roaring ]
- Sure you do.

1469
01:48:36,406 --> 01:48:38,874
You're some kind of big, fat,
smart Bug, aren't ya?

1470
01:48:38,966 --> 01:48:40,797
[ Roaring ]

1471
01:48:42,366 --> 01:48:44,357
Come on.

1472
01:48:54,806 --> 01:48:56,922
This is Roughneck Two-Zero.

1473
01:48:57,006 --> 01:49:00,362
Brain Bug sighted
moving west of grid five.

1474
01:49:02,646 --> 01:49:05,114
- Run!
- [ Roaring, Screeching ]

1475
01:49:32,886 --> 01:49:35,241
[ Screaming ]
No!

1476
01:49:35,326 --> 01:49:38,716
- Give me the nuke!
- You tryin' to be a hero, Watkins?

1477
01:49:40,726 --> 01:49:43,957
I'm tryin' to kill some Bugs, sir.
Get outta here!

1478
01:49:44,046 --> 01:49:47,163
- [ Beeping ]
- Get outta here!

1479
01:49:48,486 --> 01:49:50,124
Move!

1480
01:49:54,086 --> 01:49:56,441
Come on! You like that?
You like that?

1481
01:49:56,486 --> 01:49:58,397
Come on!
You want some more?

1482
01:50:02,086 --> 01:50:05,123
You like that? You like that?
You want some more?

1483
01:50:11,006 --> 01:50:12,758
Come on! Come on--

1484
01:50:24,206 --> 01:50:26,401
- Aaaah!
- Down! Down!

1485
01:50:41,486 --> 01:50:43,238
Come on, Carmen.

1486
01:50:47,486 --> 01:50:50,284
[ Shouting, Cheering, Faint ]

1487
01:50:54,846 --> 01:50:57,314
- [ Trooper ] We did it!
- [ Trooper ] Come on!

1488
01:50:59,366 --> 01:51:01,960
[ Cheering, Shouting Continue ]

1489
01:51:02,046 --> 01:51:06,039
- What's goin' on? Come on!
- They got it!

1490
01:51:17,486 --> 01:51:19,795
[ Grunting ]

1491
01:51:26,606 --> 01:51:28,915
[ Snarling ]

1492
01:51:33,326 --> 01:51:35,157
[ Officer ]
Quiet!

1493
01:51:35,246 --> 01:51:37,077
[ Shouting Quiets ]

1494
01:51:37,166 --> 01:51:39,475
[ Growling ]

1495
01:51:47,166 --> 01:51:49,441
What's it thinking, Colonel?

1496
01:51:49,526 --> 01:51:51,835
[ Whimpering ]

1497
01:52:01,086 --> 01:52:03,395
[ Rumbling, Gurgling ]

1498
01:52:06,246 --> 01:52:08,123
It's afraid.

1499
01:52:09,166 --> 01:52:11,919
- It's afraid!
- [ Cheering, Shouting ]

1500
01:52:11,966 --> 01:52:14,400
[ Weapons Firing ]

1501
01:52:15,766 --> 01:52:17,722
Whoo!
Yeah!

1502
01:52:17,766 --> 01:52:20,121
[ Carmen ]
Carl! Carl! Hey!

1503
01:52:20,206 --> 01:52:23,004
Well, look who's here.
You made it. Good.

1504
01:52:23,086 --> 01:52:26,237
It was you, wasn't it?
You told me how to find Carmen.

1505
01:52:26,326 --> 01:52:27,839
Well, that's classified.

1506
01:52:29,806 --> 01:52:32,604
You know, whenever the three of us
are together...

1507
01:52:32,686 --> 01:52:35,484
I feel like things
might just work out.

1508
01:52:35,566 --> 01:52:37,397
I hope you're right, Carmen.

1509
01:52:37,486 --> 01:52:39,317
We've got one of their Brains now.

1510
01:52:39,406 --> 01:52:42,603
Pretty soon we'll know how they think,
and then we'll know how to beat them.

1511
01:52:42,686 --> 01:52:44,517
One day it will all be over...

1512
01:52:44,606 --> 01:52:47,404
and everyone will forget
that this was the moment.

1513
01:52:47,486 --> 01:52:49,317
This is when it turned.

1514
01:52:49,406 --> 01:52:54,605
And it wasn't the mighty Fleet.
It wasn't some fancy new weapon.

1515
01:52:54,686 --> 01:52:57,564
- [ Cheering Continues ]
- [ Zim Laughing ]

1516
01:52:57,606 --> 01:53:00,962
It was a drill instructor named Zim
who captured a Brain.

1517
01:53:01,046 --> 01:53:02,843
Come on! Come on!

1518
01:53:02,926 --> 01:53:05,076
Zim.

1519
01:53:06,326 --> 01:53:08,635
He got him! Yeah!

1520
01:53:08,726 --> 01:53:12,435
Zim! Zim got the Bug!
Zim got the Bug, man!

1521
01:53:12,486 --> 01:53:15,637
- Good job, Sergeant.
- Thank you, sir.

1522
01:53:15,726 --> 01:53:18,399
That'd be Private, sir.

1523
01:53:18,486 --> 01:53:20,363
Carry on, Private.

1524
01:53:20,446 --> 01:53:23,040
- Yes, sir!
- [ Cheering Continues ]

1525
01:53:26,606 --> 01:53:29,916
[ Narrator ] What mysteries
will the Brain Bug reveal?

1526
01:53:30,006 --> 01:53:33,282
Federal scientists are working
around the clock to probe its secrets.

1527
01:53:33,366 --> 01:53:35,641
- [ Drill Whirring ]
- [ Roaring ]

1528
01:53:35,726 --> 01:53:38,638
Once we understand the Bug,
we will defeat it.

1529
01:53:38,686 --> 01:53:40,563
[ Loud Roaring ]

1530
01:53:43,926 --> 01:53:45,723
We have the ships.

1531
01:53:45,806 --> 01:53:48,445
We have the weapons.

1532
01:53:48,526 --> 01:53:50,357
We need soldiers.

1533
01:53:50,446 --> 01:53:52,880
Soldiers like
Lieutenant Stack Lumbrezer...

1534
01:53:52,926 --> 01:53:54,803
Over the target area now, Captain.

1535
01:53:54,846 --> 01:53:56,723
[ Narrator ]
and Captain Carmen Ibanez.

1536
01:53:56,766 --> 01:53:59,599
This is the captain speaking.
All personnel prepare for drop.

1537
01:53:59,646 --> 01:54:02,479
[ Narrator ]
Soldiers like Private Ace Levy
and Lieutenant John Rico.

1538
01:54:02,526 --> 01:54:05,279
Come on, you apes!
You wanna live forever?

1539
01:54:05,366 --> 01:54:07,197
- [ Shouting ]
- [ Narrator ] We need you all.

1540
01:54:07,286 --> 01:54:10,676
Service guarantees citizenship.
